(11, 274, 'PCC2025103', 'StudyIQIAS, Clarity for UPSC by Dr. Shivin, OnlyIAS Extended, Vajiram & Ravi', 'No', 'NA', 'NA', 1, 'Yes, major stress is coming from two reasons. 1) Few questions I am lacking knowledge to attempt 2) Not able to recollect at times even though I have gone through it previously 3) Time management since I spend quite sometime to analyse each question before answering them and that is taking me lot of time and not able to increase my no of questions attempted.', '1) Giving test on OMR sheets, gives a real feel of exam.\r\n2) Dedicated test on a scheduled time helped me build that discipline.\r\n3) Questions asked in tests are of the similar pattern to the PYQs so getting habbituated with facing the challenges in attempting difficult and not so straight forward questions what we predict to be asked in the actual exam.', '1) Not able to increase my no of questions attempted\r\n2) Shortfall of either recollecting some topics or missing out of knowledge', 'For mock test, my approach is to read the questions twice or thrice along with options so that I get to understand what is in between the lines and do not miss out the trick', 1, 'Currently I am still working and serving my notice period in office which would end by March 19th.\r\nOn weekdays, I seldom get time to study, but make sure I study 3-4 hours after I return back from office.\r\nOn weekends, I set a target of studying 10 hours so that i could revise what I covered on weekdays, give exams and take a quick look at the current affairs for that week.', '2025-02-22 17:29:48', '2025-02-22 17:29:48', NULL),
