(26, 54, 'OST2025166', 'DOWN TO EARTH, MONGABAY, SANSAD TV, ONLY IAS, DRISHTI IAS', 'NO', NULL, NULL, 2, 'YES, SOMETIMES WHEN I AM SOLVING HISTORY AND ECONOMICS PAPERS. HOWEVER, I AM ABLE TO CONTROL IT. IT DOES NOT OVERWHELM ME.', '1) MARK IN THE OMR AFTER 50 QUESTIONS TO GIVE BRAIN SOME REST SO THAT I CAN SOLVE THE NEXT 50 QUESTIONS. 2) UNDERLINING WHILE READING TO PREVENT MISSING OUT OF KEY WORDS. 3) TO DO 70-80 QUESTIONS TO PREVENT MORE NEGATIVE MARKS. 4) TO EAT A CHOCOLATE BEFORE EXAM TO MID EXAM EXHAUSTION AWAY.', '1)MISSING OUT WORDS WHILE READING QUESTIONS. 2) MARKING WRONG IN THE OMR. 3)LACK OF REVISION IN A NUMBER OF TOPICS AND FEW NEW TOPICS.', 'NO, BUT NOW I HAVE INCORPORATED - SOLVE THE PAPER IN 2-3 ROUNDS DEPENDING ON MY KNOWLEDGE GAP AND COMFORT WITH THE SUBJECT.', 1, '10 AM-2 PM - CORE SUBJECT FOR EXAM\r\n3 PM - 5 PM - CORE SUBJECT FOR EXAM\r\n5:30 PM - 8 PM - CURRENT AFFAIR\r\n8 PM - 9 PM - CSAT\r\n11 PM - 2:30 PM - REVISION', '2025-02-22 18:07:00', '2025-02-22 18:07:00', NULL),
