(37, 67, 'OST2025163', 'IAS PCS Pathshala, Shivin Sir, Naman Shrivastava, Manoj Jindal Sir, OnlyIAS extended, sleepy classes', 'No', 'NA', 'NA', 0, 'I have given many competitive exams before so i didn\'t experience stress during mock tests, even in classroom environment in government schools. However due to poor facilities in final exam centre i couldn\'t help but feel stressed. Also, i had got a heatstroke but proper preparation helped me to stay calm during CSAT. But i have experienced complacency if i get a certain number of questions right at the beginning which I haven\'t been able to eliminate yet. I feel stressed in the later part of the exam due to which i am unable to complete my second revision of the paper and go for third revisions.', 'With very little revision i am able to retain information and make a healthy amount of good guesses compared to my previous attempt. Also my home environment is volatile and unpleasant, and even during the worst conditions i have been able to retain my composure and give my paper satisfactorily.', 'I am unable to complete reading the entire explanation pdf, but I\'m slowly increasing my speed. The home environment sometimes makes me a little too comfortable and i hope i don\'t get used to that specifically. I have also mismarked in the omr sheet and gotten plenty of wrong guesses in my weak papers who\'s basics I haven\'t covered too well, so i am working on subject specific strategies and risk taking.', 'I go through the entire paper at once and mark the questions I know and circle the ones i am.75-25, 50-50 or 25-75 sure. I then proceed to mark the sure ones on my omr and then go for the second revision marking the decided 75-25 and 50-50 ones. I mark them in the omr next. If time remains, i go through the 25-75 ones and read the ones i left untouched, if i get an epiphany towards the end of the exam (which sometimes happens) and i mark them if any.', 1, '8 30 - 10 30, 11 - 1:30, 4-6 30 7-10 30, 12 - 1 study timings. Th