(48, 265, 'PCC2025202', 'Clarity for UPSC by Dr Shivin, Mrunal Patel Unacademy, Drishti, PWOnlyIAS, StudyIQ', 'No', NULL, NULL, 0, 'Yes. Even though I started preparing seriously in 2025, when I performed poorly in the first two weeks, I truly felt that I was at the bottom of the race. My Geography comprehensive test performance was also poor, which demotivated me greatly.', 'I was able to understand and realise that I had to work extra hard to keep up with aspirants who have entered the race at an earlier stage and it only motivated me to work twice as hard. I was also able to get in touch with other aspirants who are at a similar level of preparation which made group study possible.', 'That I was not reading the entire question before answering them or even marking them incorrectly in the OMR. In most of the incorrectly answered questions though, I had lacked conceptual clarity, which is something I am currently working on.', 'Identifying microthemes that I need to work more on and only focusing on them a day before the mock test and during the night I would only focus on question solving.', 1, '7-8 AM: CSAT (1 hr)\r\n8-9 AM: Newspaper and Current Affairs (1 hr)\r\n9:30 AM: 1st GS subject of the week (3 hrs)\r\n3:00 PM: 2nd GS subject of the week (3 hrs) \r\n6:00 PM: PYQ/Mock Question Solving (2-3hrs)\r\n(All days before the day of the mock test)', '2025-02-22 18:58:46', '2025-02-22 18:58:46', NULL),
