(50, 128, '20251109', 'Dr. shivin, PW economics marathon series, unacademy Mrunal Sir WIN series, studyIQ IAS, Vision IAS, UPSCprep, Firstpost for news', 'No', 'But for Law optional I have enrolled into De Facto Law', 'Daily classes for Law Optional, and a test series.', 0, 'A little bit of worry but nothing too much', 'It has helped me understand the syllabus better and it has eradicated the fear of sitting for exams from me', 'I need to increase my knowledge base so that I can attempt more sure shot answers.', 'Qualitative approach- increase accuracy, target less number of questions and focus on getting the limited number of questions correct in the first go.', 1, 'I try to stick to this schedule but most days I am only able to study productively for 8 to 9 hours only. \r\nTHE SCHEDULE:\r\nWake up at 6:30 am. Freshen up. \r\n7:00am- 9:00am: first study session on primary subject \r\n9:30-11:30am- 2nd session on primary subject \r\n12:00-1:00pm- PYQ\r\n3:00 -5:00pm- Current affairs/CSAT once a week\r\n6:00-8:00pm- 2nd primary subject \r\n8:30-10:30pm- 2nd primary subject \r\n11pm -12pm- revision.\r\nI read the newspaper before going to sleep', '2025-02-22 19:00:26', '2025-02-22 19:00:26', NULL),
