(65, 114, '20251050', 'None', 'No', 'Not applicable', 'Not applicable', 1, 'Yes, while attempting mocks at SNTCSSC, I sometimes experience a mental paralysis where simple sentences stop making sense to me, that costs me time. Also while marking options after I\'ve marked and gone for the next question sometimes it dawns on me that I have marked the wrong option and need to correct it on the OMR.', 'My analytical skills are good, I can cover 90% of the paper, I do not stick to a question if it bothers me and go on to solve others and then come back later to solve it.', 'I mark some options too fast, later when I\'m solving another question the correct answer dawns upon me.', 'I keep flipping the pages, mark whatever I can going through them, some which I feel need me to think and are solvable I mark them for later review and towards the end of the test I come upon them.', 1, 'I wake up around 6am, study for 2hours. Then I get out for the institute and return home around 8pm, I straightaway sit to study and study till 12am with a 30 min break in between for dinner.\r\nOn days that are off and I get to stay at home, I study from 6am - 11am at a stretch then take a break for 30 mins. Next from 11.30-1.30pm I study again. 1.30pm to 3.30 is a big break for me where I do my lunch as well. From 3.30 to 4.30 slot I generally feel very tired so my productivity drops in this time. From 6.30 to 11.30pm again I get a energy boost to study and in between I take a break of half an hour to do my dinner.', '2025-02-22 19:51:41', '2025-02-22 19:51:41', NULL),
