(72, 217, 'PCC2025189', 'Understand UPSC by Satyam Jain, Dr. Shivin Choudhary', 'PreVail', 'Understand UPSC', 'PreVail, MAD (MCQ Aptitude Development), Prelims Test Series and Recorded Classes,', 1, 'From 2021- 2024 I always tended to fall sick from Feb- to April, this resulted in the loss of vital time, which used to cause deep-rooted anxiety as I was never able to revise the syllabus on time, this used to cause stomach issues like loose motion, indigestion, acidity especially in the scorching heat of April and May. This digestion issue ruins my Paper II when my anxiety level is at its peak, apart from that wrong food choices and availability further add fuel to the snowball of errors. This time, I am doing my best to identify and rectify these issues.', 'Understanding my strengths and weaknesses, especially the type of question to attempt and leave. The post-analysis summary acts as source material.', 'Dilemma between taking the high risk high reward or low attempt and mediocre marks.', 'I try applying for MAD tricks but often get confused in the exam apart from the basic knowledge that fetches me very low marks and usually while attempting more I have been losing more marks.', 1, '7 am-10 am- Revision past exams\r\n11 am- 1 PM- Current Affairs\r\n2:30 pm- 4:30 pm CSAT\r\n6:00 Pm- 9 PM Test Subjects/ online classes', '2025-02-22 20:29:48', '2025-02-22 20:29:48', NULL),
