(97, 125, '20251065', 'Madhukar Kotawe (CSAT)', 'No', 'Not Applicable', 'Not Applicable', 0, 'Yes. The level of the same keeps changing in proportion to the type of preparation I have been able to do for the same test.', '1. The confidence to appear for tests even if the level of my preparation is not to my utmost satisfaction\r\n2. Handling questions that are confusing\r\n3. Prioritizing and understanding which questions to attempt and which not to', '1. Taking unnecessary risks\r\n2. Knowledge gap\r\n3. Incorrect elimination strategy\r\n4. Necessity of further revisions\r\n5. Building further base in Current Affairs', 'Yes. \r\n1. Answer those which i am completely sure o in the first round\r\n2. Answer all the 50:50 questions\r\n3. Selectively answer the 25:75 questions\r\n4. Not attempting on blind guesses', 1, '9:30-11:30 am - Slot one (GS)\r\n12:00 - 2:00 pm - Slot two (GS)\r\n3:00 - 5:00 pm - Slot Three (CSAT)\r\n7:30- 8:30 pm - Slot four (Current Affairs)\r\n9:00 - 10:00 pm - slot four (PYQ analysis occasionally)', '2025-02-22 22:34:01', '2025-02-22 22:34:01', NULL),
(98, 202, '20252076', 'Parcham Classes (for Geography, Richa ma\'am) \r\nOnly IAS (History and Art and Culture) (Abhishek Srivastava)', 'No', NULL, NULL, 0, 'I haven\'t yet appeared for the upsc prelims yet, however during the mock tests I appeared, I usually feel a bit nervous during the CSAT tests as my scores are lagging behind in that section. Science and Tech basic concepts and art and culture section of the paper usually overwhelms me.', 'I believe that due to the tests, regular revison and practice takes place, which helps me build my confidence. I should also focus on basics and conceptual clarity', 'CSAT needs more daily practice and also more revision of basic concepts needs to be put in. Also, I realised that some CAs can be solved using conceptual knowledge, however my application part in the concepts seem a little weaker. I also get overwhelmed by CAs in different subjects and lack of revision of CAs is a hurdle.', 'My strategy is that I usually try to integrate the Prelims and Mains preparation as I search for the overall PYQ on the topics. I also follow the Current Affairs closely to link the static and the current portion, however it also becomes a little overwhelming to balance basics with CA.', 1, '8 a.m. - 10 a.m. : UPSC Revision of any 2 subjects ( usually my strong subjects like Polity, Geography and Economics)\r\nOr \r\nAttempting UPSC full length PYQ (on weekends usually) \r\n11 a.m. -5 p.m. : College \r\n6 p.m. - 8 p.m : College Studies\r\n8 p.m. - 8:30 p.m. : The Hindu Newspaper \r\n9:00- 2:00 p.m. : UPSC (2-3 subjects like Science and Tech, Environment, Art and Culture, CSAT mapmaking, diagrams)', '2025-02-22 22:38:39', '2025-02-22 22:38:39', NULL),
