(171, 136, '20251078', 'StudyIQ IAS, Drishti IAS, Clarity for UPSC by Dr. Shivin', 'No', 'Not Applicable', 'Not Applicable', 0, 'Yes, I often get anxious while the mock tests begin but I gradually get calmer as the test progresses. By the end, I retain my composure.', 'I get a clearer perspective of my preparation trajectory. Also, the answer key shared after the test provided me with great insight into the subject matter.', 'The mistakes that I make in mock tests stem either from my lack of knowledge of the subject or my inability to eliminate between the closest options.', 'Yes, for the static portions, I focus mainly on enhancing my knowledge base, and for current-based questions I employ the elimination technique. Also I prefer quantity over quality, I attempt as many questions as possible.', 1, 'In the morning-afternoon study session(9;00-12:00) I dedicate 3 hours to studying the subjects that I find the most difficult and if I am attending the classes then I study for an hour (8;00-9:00). \r\n2:00-3;30 For current affairs\r\n6:00-9:00 Revision of older topics along with I study less-challenging new topics. I take 30 mins breaks in between.', '2025-02-24 10:47:20', '2025-02-24 10:47:20', NULL),
