(220, 242, 'PCC2025001', 'The Hindu, OnlyIAS, StudyIQ, Drishti, Unacademy, Adda 24*7 (Csat), Manuj Jindal IAS', 'No', NULL, NULL, 2, 'Yes my anxiety is based on whether I will be able to complete my attempts within 2 hours. Due to this I can\'t follow any pattern for paper completion. I attempt first 20-25 then go back to 100-80 then come to the middle of the paper. Such haphazard way gets time consuming and I panic further. My anxiety further rises when I am unable to attempt consecutively 3-4 questions or when I have to leave the entire question because of my unfamiliarity with any one option. Such anxiety and stress has also brought fatigue in my preparation which is hindering me back further.', 'To read basic ncerts thoroughly, to analyse pyq ( especially of csat), mock test explanations are helpful as they act as further content for mains also, time management and increase in concentration. My focus has also improved as I can sit continuously for 4 hours and I have been trying to attempt the mocks sequentially. I successfully have achieved that since the past 2 mocks.', 'Lack of revision, lack of routine, no proper direction month wise and day wise, lack of crisp and compact sources', 'Previously I didn\'t but recently I do. I go through the entire paper, categorize it into sure, unsure, partially sure then attempt the sure ones first, partially sure ones next and unsure ones later as they require guessing and elimination', 1, '6:30- Wake up\r\n6:40- 10:30- Mock Test subject \r\n10:40-11:30- Mock Test explanation ( revision) \r\n11:45-1:30- Revision of static subjects\r\n2:30-5- CSAT \r\n5:30-9 - CA\r\n9:15- 11:45- Mock test subject\r\n12-2- Optional', '2025-02-24 19:18:06', '2025-02-24 19:18:06', NULL),
