(227, 23, 'OST2025071', 'STUDY IQ IAS By Prashant Dhaman, Mrunal\'s Economy channel, Unacademy You tube channels, Sudarshan Gurjar\'s Youtube channel for Geography & places in news & Environment.', 'Online Coa', 'Unacademy', 'Online subscription for classes & testseries.', 1, 'Yes in actual Prelims test I face these even after giving mock tests and revision. I tend to have a FOMO as well as most of the topics which have studied or practiced PYQs I forget them and mark the wrong option. somehow I feel that my brain stops working in the real exam because of stress, anxiety and nervousness.', 'Some questions are actually doable which I have studied and know about them sureshot.\r\n1. Paper can be completed on time if time management done properly during exam.\r\n2. Revision are must\r\n3. Not to go behind question which I donot feel comfortable with at the first site.', '1. Lack of Revision. \r\n2. Spending too much time on one question which I think is doable & have studied about it but not able to answer in exam due to confusion.', 'No strategy as such.', 1, 'I have not made any Specific time table for different subjects.\r\n1 hour for PYQ\'s and analysis.\r\n1 hour for Current affairs.\r\n1 hour for Economy.\r\n2 hours for History. \r\n1 hour for Polity.\r\n The subjects are replaced once they are completed.\r\nWith regards to CSAT I donot practice it on a daily basis since it is very time consuming  and I feel difficulty in practicing Maths problems being from Arts background . However I practice it occasionally that too stuff other than Maths.', '2025-02-24 19:28:33', '2025-02-24 19:28:33', NULL),
