(229, 164, '20252019', 'Toppers Talk, Toppers interview, Motivational Channels', 'No', NULL, NULL, 0, 'Yes everytime, I am usually \r\nan over stressed and over hyper person but during the mock tests i only feel little pressured on completing the paper on time.', 'Long study duration', NULL, 'There is no specific as such other than revision and practice', 1, 'Morning- Studying the subject which i have got exams in upcoming week\r\nAfternoon - continuing with the previous ones also with magazines\r\nEvening - studying some different subjects', '2025-02-24 19:31:53', '2025-02-24 19:31:53', NULL),
(230, 137, '20251079', 'It varies according to subjects.', 'No', NULL, NULL, 0, 'Not actually  nervous but I feel  extremely sad when I am unable to complete few chapters of mock tests', 'It is essential to improve our preparation and judge my present conditions.', 'Negative marking.When I am  confident on a particular  questions  I mark but there always remains some questions  which I make mistakes.I think I need a little bit more revision.Although  I am  studying current affairs,I feel after giving exam I need to improve it.I am having a time management  problem .', 'Study chapter wise and solving pyqs,trying to solve previous  mock test questions and see the mistakes', 1, 'Morning 5-7 a.m-Csat  ,7-8 a.m grammar(currently for placement)  9:30 to 12:30 a.m for preparing subjects given in every week mock tests ,12:30-2:30 p.mclasses for internship ,3:30-5:00 p.m-coding and doing assignments  for internship.5-7 :30p.m College studies,7:30-8:30 p.m-Newspaper,8:30-9:30  p.m -Dinner  and then online meditation class.after -9:30 to 11:00 p.m current affairs.This is the schedule when I do not go to college.Since ,I give 2-3 pre semester tests on each subjects ,I am unable to follow my schedule on exam day in college and day before my exam day.', '2025-02-24 19:34:59', '2025-02-24 19:34:59', NULL),
(231, 98, '20251020', 'ONLY IAS, DR. SHIVIN ( SARTHI IAS),', 'NOT YET', 'NO', 'NOT YET', 0, 'YES EVERYTIME WHEN I HAVE SEEN MY MOCK TESTS RESULT', 'WHERE I AM STANDING NOW AND FROM THAT PLACE HOW CAN I IMPROVE MY RANKS AND RESULTS.', 'LACK OF REVISION AND DUE TO THIS I FALL IN THE TRAP OF SILLY MISTAKES AND WRONG GUESING SENSE.', 'NOT YET', 1, 'I WAKE AT 7AM AND THEN I CAME LIBRARY AT 8AM FROM THIS TO TIL 11 AM I STUDIED MY FIRST SLOT OF THE DAY THEN I TOOL 1 BREAK FOR 30 MIN AND THEN AGAIN I STARTED MY 2ND SLOT FROM 11.30 TO 2.PM FOR LUNCH THEN AGAIN I TOOK MY 1 HRS LONG BREAK FOR LUNCH AND SOMETIMES BATHING THEN AGAIN STARTED AT 3 PM TO TIL 6PM MY 3RD SLOT ( BUT IN THIS TIME I FEEL SLEEPY DUE TO LUNCH AND BUT  STILL I CONTINUE MY PROCESS) THEN AGAIN I TOOK MY EVENING SNACKS OR TEA BRAKE FOR 1 HRS THEN FROM 7PM MY 4TH SLOT IS START TO TILL 9 PM THEN I TOOK 1HRS BREAK FOR DINNER & PHONE CALLS WITH MY FAMILY THEN FROM 10.30PM TO 11.30 MY LAST 1HRS 5TH SLOT AND BY 1 AM I SLEPT EVERYDAY.', '2025-02-24 19:40:51', '2025-02-24 19:40:51', NULL),
(232, 35, 'OST2025117', 'ZETA AXIS, CONVERT IAS, ONLY IAS', 'NO', 'NOT APPLICABLE', 'NOT APPLICABLE', 3, 'INITIALLY YES DURING MY FIRST YEAR BUT GRADUALLY IT HAS SUBSIDED', 'LEARNING HOW TO READ , ANALYSE AND COMPLETE THE QUESTIONS WITHIN THE STIPULATED TIME', 'REVISE THE MOCKS MORE SINCE VARIOUS QUESTIONS HAD COME DIRECTLY FROM THEM, ATTEMPT MORE QUESTIONS AND NOT FALL FOR FOMO MATERIAL', 'YES. I TRY TO ATTEMPT FIRST 50 AND THEN FILL UP MY OMR AND THEN ATTEMPT NEXT 50 AND FILL UP MY OMR. THEN ATTEMPT THE REMAINING ONES', 1, '10 HOURS DAILY WITH BREAKS IN BETWEEN', '2025-02-24 19:40:53', '2025-02-24 19:40:53', NULL),
(233, 179, '20252038', 'None', 'No', NULL, NULL, 2, 'Only for subjects whose syllabus remains incomplete or where I have not done revisions.', 'I was able to identify my weaknesses and worked on them.', NULL, 'No', 1, 'I start for the coaching at 10, sometimes 10:30. Thereafter I attend the regular classes and take notes. From 5:30 in the evening till 9 I self prepare the same subject. Thereafter I head home and after having dinner, I start with daily current affairs for 1 hour and two hours for my optional papers.', '2025-02-24 19:51:26', '2025-02-24 19:51:26', NULL),
(234, 170, '20252029', 'none', 'no', NULL, NULL, 0, 'Yes, during mock test in class there are many times where i am not able to recall and sometimes gets confused between the options for example while giving geography test even after revising so many times I don\'t know why i am still getting the answers wrong this has often led to nervous breakdown and often caused trauma and even made myself doubt my own abilities and many times i found options confusing', 'to embrace unpredictability', 'not able to recall at that specific moment anxiety and panic in my mind', 'no', 1, '10am to 2 pm 1st study session\r\n3pm to 4:30 pm 2nd study session\r\n6pm to 10 pm 3rd and final study session', '2025-02-24 19:52:51', '2025-02-24 19:52:51', NULL),
(235, 298, 'PCC2025118', 'Study IQ IAS, Gagan Pratap maths, Drishti IAS, Amit Sengupta, PW Only IAS, Magnet Brains, bookstawa.', 'No.', NULL, NULL, 2, 'Nervousness and panic. Most of the time I\'m thinking about time is running out and I can\'t complete the paper.', 'Focusing on the most important parts, the core portions in subjects from where the questions are formed. \r\nLearning how to calm down own self in the pressure situations. \r\nLearning how to make strategies for complete the syllabus.', 'Lack of revisions, maintaing intensity and focus throughout the examination.', 'Solve questions one by one without \r\nreading the whole paper at first, give the exam in the worst conditions to be habituated with the tough, Meditation, exercise.', 1, '7 am - 1 pm - subjects \r\n3.30 pm - 5.30 pm - current affairs \r\n6 pm - 8 pm - revision \r\n8.15 pm - 10 pm - CSAT', '2025-02-24 19:54:56', '2025-02-24 19:54:56', NULL),
