(239, 303, 'PCC2025246', 'IAS pathsala, PW only IAS, study iq,KSG IAS', 'No', 'Not applicable', 'Not applicable', 0, 'Fear of not completing the test in proper time,concern about not knowing or remembering specific concept', 'The mock tests help me in time managing and to develop a strategic approach also it helps me identifying my strength and weakness', 'Lack of revision,wrong mark in OMR on hurry,read the question in hurry,eliminate at least two options but made a mistake', 'No', 1, '7AM-11:30=the main subject \r\n11:30-1:30=monthly magazine\r\n3:00pm-4:30pm=optional\r\n7:00pm-9:00pm=Revise the backlog\r\n9:00pm-10:00pm=CSAT practice \r\n9:00-', '2025-02-24 20:21:48', '2025-02-24 20:21:48', NULL),
(240, 159, '20252103', 'StudyIQ IAS, Apni Pathshala, Abhinay Maths', 'No', NULL, 'Not Applicable', 0, 'Yes. The vastness of the syllabus dawns upon me at the last moment causing self doubt and anxious conditions.', 'Time management', 'The requirement to work harder, to stay calm and not be in a rush', 'Not Applicable', 1, 'I try to dedicate a certain number of hours for a particular subject, attempt to solve the related questions, before moving on to another subject. As I am pursuing my Masters simultaneously hence it has been difficult to allot an exact specific time for UPSC preparation as for now. I\'m  working on it.', '2025-02-24 20:35:45', '2025-02-24 20:35:45', NULL),
(241, 231, 'PCC2025256', 'AMIT SENGUPTA,PW OnlyIAS, HARSHIT DWIVEDI EDUCATION,STUDYIQ IAS,SLEEPY CLASSES IAS,PIB INDIA,VISION IAS,MURNAL PATEL UNACADEMY,IAS PCS PATHSHALA', 'NO', NULL, NULL, 0, 'Yes, I experienced stress, anxiety, and nervousness while taking mock tests, especially due to time pressure and fear of making mistakes. However, I am working on managing it through better revision, time management, and staying calm during the exam', 'Mock tests have given me confidence and helped me analyze my performance and mistakes. They allow me to identify weak areas, improve time management, and develop better exam strategies.', 'After taking mock tests, I realized that I make mistakes due to time mismanagement, misinterpretation of questions, and lack of proper revision of certain topics. I also noticed that I sometimes struggle with accuracy in tricky questions and need to improve my elimination technique in multiple-choice questions.', 'To improve my performance, I follow a structured strategy for mock tests. I attempt questions in rounds, starting with the ones I am most confident about. I also practice time management by setting a time limit for each section and ensure proper revision before the test. After each mock test, I analyze my mistakes, revise weak areas, and focus on improving accuracy.', 1, 'Morning (7:00 AM – 10:00 AM): Revision of previous topics and current affairs.\r\nMidday (11:00 AM – 2:00 PM): Focused study on core subjects \r\nAfternoon (3:00 PM – 5:00 PM): CSAT,Practice PYQs,\r\nEvening (7:00 PM – 9:00 PM): Attend classes \r\nNight (9:30 PM – 11:00 PM): Newspaper Reading, Self-revision,', '2025-02-24 20:40:59', '2025-02-24 20:40:59', NULL),
(242, 144, '20251104', 'NOT APPLICABLE', 'NO', 'NOT APPLICABLE', 'NOT APPLICABLE', 0, 'Yes, felt like need to revise more', 'Practice will make me succeed', 'TIME MANAGEMENT DURING EXAM AND HURRYING DURING READING THE QUESTIONS', 'No', 1, 'DEPENDS ON MY TO DO LIST OF THE DAY', '2025-02-24 20:46:53', '2025-02-24 20:46:53', NULL),
(243, 8, 'OST2025026', 'Wholeheartedly I do not follow any channels, if a face any doubts I refer to Unacademy, Study IQ\'s yt channels and for exam strategies I recently started following Dr. Shivin\'s channel', 'No', 'NA', 'NA', 3, 'Not during Mock tests but during UPSC prelims if I fail to answer a series of questions (lets say 8-10) I start to panic and I become nervous. While the final exam approaching I feel extremely stressed.', 'This year mock tests specially that performence analysis sheet helped me to pin point my weak areas.', 'I need some conceptual clarity in certain sections of Economics, Need to work on ancient medieval history and art & culture, I need to revise the magazines, I have collect deeper level of informations(E.g.- For National Parks I\'ve to remember not only the states they belong to but also the river banks they are situated at).', 'I try to attempt only those questions where I\'m 100% certain and avoid any \'lucky guesses\', in next exam I try to have more grasps over the portions I had left(and had answered wrong) in previous exam', 1, '9:00 am - 12:30 am (Statics + Newspaper), 2:00 pm - 5 pm(Most of the times Statics and sometimes CSAT), 6:00 pm - 9:30 pm (Statics) , 11:00 pm - 1:00 am (covering what is left from daily target and planning for next day)', '2025-02-24 20:47:51', '2025-02-24 20:47:51', NULL),
