(285, 235, 'PCC2025139', 'Clarity for UPSC by Dr. Shivin , UPSCprep.com , IAS PCS Pathshala', 'Yes', 'Dr.UPSC', NULL, 0, 'I felt anxious when there were only 10 to 15 minutes left and I still had to attempt more than 15 questions. I often find myself in a dilemma, wondering whether the options I choose are correct. I believe my confidence level should be higher when making these choices but don\'t find the way to make it happen.', 'I realized that my initial guesses were not very accurate, so I need to revise more. In certain topics, I felt confident, but while taking mock tests, I discovered that I need to study those areas in more depth. So mock tests are playing a crucial role in my preparation.', 'Not revised properly and sometimes, I missed the demands of the question regarding whether to choose the correct or incorrect option and  giving a lot of time initially to make a choice specifically in knowing topics , which makes me incapable of attempting all the questions in time.', 'Reading topics according to syllabus and making sure not to miss more weighted topics and reviewing pyqs .', 1, '9.00 - 12.00  AM :  GS \r\n\r\n1.00 - 2.00 PM : GS \r\n\r\n3.30 - 6.00 PM : Anthropology Optional \r\n\r\n7.00 - 8.30 PM : CSAT\r\n\r\n8.30 - 9.30 PM : CA\r\n\r\n9.30 - 11.00 PM : GS', '2025-02-25 00:12:52', '2025-02-25 00:12:52', NULL),
(286, 132, '20251070', 'Study IQ , sansad TV', 'No', 'No', 'Nil', 0, 'No', 'NA', 'NA', 'NA', 1, 'Wake up @ 10 AM\r\nGet ready and start study by 10:30AM -1:30PM  : 3 HRS\r\nComplete Lunch by 2:30 PM\r\n\r\nStudy 2:30 - 5:30 : 3 HRS\r\n\r\nTake break 5:30 - 6:30  \r\n\r\n6:30 - 9:30 study \r\n\r\n9:30  - 10:30 break \r\n\r\n10:30 - 12:30AM : study optional \r\n\r\n12:45 - 2:45 : Revision \r\n\r\nGo to sleep @ 3 AM', '2025-02-25 00:33:14', '2025-02-25 00:33:14', NULL),
(287, 199, '20252073', 'Sarrthi IAS, PW OnlyIAS, Amit Sengupta etc.', 'No', 'Not applicable', 'Not applicable', 0, 'I become a little bit anxious and nervous', 'To be calm, composed and concentrated', 'I have identified the areas which I need to study properly', 'No', 1, 'I study for 7-8 hours a day', '2025-02-25 00:53:19', '2025-02-25 00:53:19', NULL),
(288, 244, 'PCC2025053', 'Manuj Jindal, UPSCPrep.com, Unacademy, Mrunal Patel Unacademy', 'No', NULL, NULL, 0, 'Yes, I get stressed more from the fear that I am unable to read the subject properly and have cut corners. Also, I have faced difficulties sleeping the day before the exam because of my anxiety level, and I have given a few exams without sleeping at all the night before.', 'That I was able to answer from the section I studied well and managed to go through all the 100 questions within two hours.', 'That I am not revising enough and also sometimes making mistakes from the same topics.', 'As it is two exams every Sunday, so I try to study current affairs in the morning and at night in two parts and spend the in between time studying the GS subjects so that I could complete all the topics from the current affairs part at least. But that strategy has not worked very well so far because I feel I am taking a lot more time making the Current Affairs notes than I should take and that is stopping me from firstly devote more time towards the GS subjects, and secondly from going through all the topics of the monthly current affairs topics list.', 1, 'Morning from 6 am or 6:30 am, study 2 hours current affairs. Then after 1 or 1.5 hours gap, study GS subjects in three different parts till evening, Study current affairs again at night but this last part does not happen more often than not.', '2025-02-25 01:57:57', '2025-02-25 01:57:57', NULL),
(289, 309, 'NST2025254', 'StudyIQ IAS', 'No', NULL, NULL, 0, 'Yes,', 'I am improving consistently, and I tell myself that I can do better if I work hard', 'inefficient Knowledge', 'I follow weekly expected topic list.', 1, 'In the Morning I read newspaper for 1 hour, then I leave for my Coaching. I come back at 7:30 P.M, then take rest for an hour. Then I do self-studies for 3 hours. after having dinner, I sit for CSAT class for about 2 hours.', '2025-02-25 02:32:00', '2025-02-25 02:32:00', NULL),
