(50, 265, 'PCC2025202', 'To attain job security and contribute to the society positively.', 'Humility and hard work. One must always stay grounded, identify areas for improvement and strive to overcome them through dedication and self reflection.', 'My father is a cancer patient currently undergoing treatment for his condition and I am hoping to take some burden off his shoulders financially so he can continue his therapy without having to think about my future.', 'During my post-graduation, I developed strong time management skills, studying/workin 14-16 hours/day. My Botany background provides a solid foundation in Environment & Ecology, enabling me to tackle related questions with ease, giving me an edge in the UPSC examination and facilitating my success.', 'I may feel apprehensive when interacting with large groups, fearing judgment or feeling overwhelmed. However, I\'m actively working to build my confidence and improve my communication skills, ensuring that I can effectively engage with diverse audiences and articulate my thoughts clearly.', 'Although my father is doing well as of now, if his health deteriorates, that would hinder my preparation process greatly.', 'As I have only started preparing in January, I am not so confident about clearing the Main Examination in this attempt.', '1. I have been actively interacting with my peers, and will try to reach out to the faculty members as much as possible to feel comfortable with communicating my thoughts better.\r\n2. My parents have provided me with a separate place to live and prepare from, so my father\'s health condition does not have to affect my study time. \r\n3. I have started preparing notes but I am still not sure whether I should start working on answer writing immediately.', 'My primary goal for this year is to clear Prelims, and I have been sticking to my routine so far. The only thing I would like to incorporate is active recalling with a study mate, which I will start doing from the second revision.', '1. My father\'s health 2. Peer pressure 3. Arguments at home 4. Calls and notifications 5. Social media', '1. By studying from my own place. 2. By refusing to meet friends until the completion of the examination. \r\n3. By not engaging \r\n4. By using my laptop\r\n5. By deactivating', 'I have been able to overcome most of these challenges so far, and will make sure things remain that way.', '2025-02-22 19:34:52', '2025-02-22 19:34:52', NULL);
