(53, 113, '20251049', 'Desire to contribute to society', '1) Discipline  2) Consistency  3) Time Management 4) Honesty  5) Good Writing skills', NULL, 'Family Support', 'Maintain Consistency', 'not maintaining the consistency', 'uncertainty & fear', 'Try to cover the syllabus and revise it as much as possible', 'Try to cover the syllabus and revise it as much as possible', '1) Uncertainties 2) Something Depression 3) Sometimes Health 4) Undiscipline 5) Unrealistic Goal 6) Social Media', 'Through meditation and self- motivation', NULL, '2025-02-22 19:54:14', '2025-02-22 19:54:14', NULL),
(54, 302, 'PCC2025009', 'Childhood dream, judging by my personality of empathy for people as well as determination to make small changes in society, my goals and morals align with the services', 'Consistency \r\nDiscipline\r\nHardwork\r\nNo fear of failure\r\nDetermination', 'I want to work for people \r\nIt has always been my dream to work in the services, I  realised I wanted nothing else but this, a life of purpose and meaning \r\nI want to work for others and a life of privilege has no meaning if I cannot serve the underprivileged\r\nI have been associated with small NGOs as a volunteer and I have seen lots of difficulties in raising the smallest amount of money for certain purposes or contributing some things, getting lots of backlash and resistance from people and I have had some other bad experiences\r\nSo what I want to do for the society is not something that can be done without a position of authority\r\nBeing in the services would give that position to transform lives of underprivileged people \r\nwhere my work will actually make an impact I other\'s lives\r\nThis is what motivates me everyday', 'I\'m Hardworking and a determined person and have no uncertainty regarding my goals', 'I need to be more consistent with my studies\r\nI need to be stop worrying about uncertainty of the future\r\nI\'m a very impatient person as well', 'I have a very weak memory and even with multiple revisions, I don\'t tend to remember things, this is the biggest obstacle that I foresee that might actually hinder me from reaching my goals', 'Lack of proper revision and incomplete syllabus', 'Doing more revisions and practicing questions and finishing syllabus as soon as possible', 'I\'m mainly focussing on cost to benefit ratio and prioritizing my subjects like that judging from the previous year questions', 'Youtube \r\nOverthinking\r\nFamily issues like financial problems\r\nProcrastination', 'Exercise and sometimes meditation\r\nTrying to keep my phone switched during study sessions\r\nJournaling sometimes', 'Youtube - to use only when needed\r\nOverthinking - meditation\r\nProcrastination- I\'ve created a reward system, if I can achieve goals for the day, I treat myself with some snacks like chocolates \r\nFamily issues - I feel there is no way out of this', '2025-02-22 19:59:52', '2025-02-22 19:59:52', NULL),
(55, 114, '20251050', 'To serve the society and find a meaning in it.', 'Discipline with flexibility', 'The need to fulfill my dreams and make my parents proud.', 'Discipline and grit.', 'Dealing with anxiety.', 'Getting too anxious at the last moment.', 'Not being able to study as much as I feel is needed but attending the classes was also necessary for me.', 'I plan to study even harder from March onwards as the classes are getting over.', 'Refer to lesser sources and cover the PYQs most.', 'Family, listening to songs, contemplating about if not then what', 'I lock myself in my room and put a timer on my phone during which I strictly use it for no other purpose but studying.', 'I am already working on that', '2025-02-22 20:01:03', '2025-02-22 20:01:03', NULL),
(56, 203, '20252078', 'Passion for serving the people.I am already in the public sector, as an Adminstrative Officer in National Insurance, in a management job role , yet I am having that huge urge to work at the ground level with people. I would always like to have that opportunity to be there beside people in their distress. Just as the armed forces are working for the country,  I would like to always put my step forward to serve my country in the best possible way I can. Looking forward to be successful as soon as possible. Will be always indebted to SNTCSSC for providing me with this incredible opportunity.', 'Discipline, Hardwork, Inquisitiveness, Awareness, Integrity, Punctuality, Responsibility', 'Passion to serve the country working at the ground level, to have that authority to make effective changes in the society for the welfare of the people.', 'Dedication, Discipline, Hardwork, Integrity, Responsibility, Punctuality, Burning desire for UPSC.', 'Overthinking,  being impulsive sometimes in stressful situations. I am trying to overcome this and I am improving.', 'Problems might come but as long as I have my attempts, nothing can stop me from achieving my goals. Even after having a job, I am dead dedicated to put forward all my sincere efforts to UPSC.', 'Time Management.  I wish I had more time.', 'Through hard work and discipline', 'To stick to my daily routine of studies and completing the daily targets and appear for all tests of SFG and revising the solutions again and again.', 'Emotional aspect sometimes, rest of my life is dedicated to UPSC', 'Through disciplined life, Hardwork and dedication', 'I am trying to overcome it. Will get over it very soon. UPSC is all I want in life.', '2025-02-22 20:05:41', '2025-02-22 20:05:41', NULL),
