(71, 293, 'PCC2025074', 'only civil servents can make an real-time impact in the society , as a head of the zila a civil servent can solve their regional problems and also the zila can be better than any other zila in the state though its impossible to reform at a whole but if an civil servent really want to do something then he can make a big impact for the people.', 'Firstly seeing the problems of the socity while reading and learning from that and every day taking oath that I will make a change in the society. sticking to the oath and truthful to myself what I am doing and how much I have done to clear civil services.', 'The problems of socity, while reading the newspaper we can see everyday a lot of problems of India sometimes there is lack of water, food, and still there are some who don\'t have home to stay I have to make sure that all the people are getting the necessary things of life. We can see there are some civil servants who are physically disabled if they can clear the exam I can also clear the exam. there are some civil servants who didn\'t had any support to study if they can I can. I have read somewhere that \"IF One can Do it then I can Do it and IF no one can do It I have to do it\" This quote makes me motivate.', 'At least being under the poverty my parents are encouraging me to do it that gives me strength.', 'Whatever I have got in my life I Thank to god for that at least I have some home and food and not physically disabled Whatever I will do that will be for society. sometimes I became angry which is not good for bureaucrats I am improving myself from that.', 'recently my sleep time has been increased a lot which will affect For me.', 'I have made only One revision till now which is a big challenge for me', 'giving time to revision.', 'Giving more time to revision, see twice while marking the omr and answer questions how much I can answer.', 'Social media, Sleep, sometimes outing with friends and talking with them when they calls.', 'unistall