(78, 217, 'PCC2025189', 'My father was a civil servant of State Govt Finance department. He served for 34 Years, he started his journey from the village and brought us to this town out of poverty. During that time he discussed with the job satisfaction of being a civil servant and most importantly dealing with the public to provide them solutions. I studied law in WBNUJS to get a proper understanding of how a law or statute works which a civil servant needs to implement in the respective field of works. I want to walk in my father\'s shoes to provide better service to the public. But when I started practicing as an advocate I came to an understanding that mere intent will not accomplish that goal but also requires the necessary power to do so. Therefore, I choose civil services for greater power and autonomy to serve the public and society which would help my intent turn into reality.', 'Consistency, discipline, clarity, focus, self-introspection and self-evaluation', 'My identity, My family, My Colleagues from NUJS who are preparing, my two juniors who cleared UPSC in 2022,', 'My Experience from 2020 to the present and the consistent little improvement I have made in my marks, My father and my family for their constant support and dedication.', '1. Confidence- After repeated failure of prelims, from last 4 years and before that stammering while speaking and the urge to avoid talking to people create a vicious circle of timidness. 2. Health- Post-Corona, there were several health issues one after another which affected each and every attempt, especially during the final month or weeks. My mind is always worried about health most of the time given the shocking incidents that occurred to me during this whole phase have left me with bitter memories.', 'Controlling Anxiety during exams when you are unable to attempt or find the correct answer, especially in CSAT, Time Management CSAT+ PAPER I, and Lack of Revision due to multiple sources which are getting culminated. Health issues during hot summer especially related to indigestion and acidity.', 'Multiple sources, e.g., Understand UPSC ORN + Most Expected Topics + Monthly Magazine. Time Management and Consistency. If I push myself too much, I feel I will fall sick. Finishing backlog revision e.g the 600 MCQs subjects.', '1. For March, I plan to increase my study timetable by 2 hours, do my best to read all my sources, and then consolidate them.\r\n2. I will cut short my time for Refreshment and Entertainment.', '1. Make a to-do list at night before the day then check the progress before going to bed.\r\n2. Sacrifice on personal comfort and test the boundaries.', '1. Social Media\r\n2. Binge-watching web series and drama.\r\n3. Hobbies like making music and astrology\r\n4. Overthinking about the future and past.\r\n5. Computer Games', '1. Deactivating the social media accounts\r\n2. Stop watching Dramas and films as pledge\r\n3. Halt my hobbies for the time being\r\n4. setting alarms for hourly update\r\n5. Uninstall all the games', 'I have identified distractions, which I will control by February. In March, I will be in full UPSC Prelims Mode.', '2025-02-22 21:49:39', '2025-02-22 21:49:39', NULL),
(79, 227, 'PCC2025232', 'I FFEL LIKE A  FISH WITHOUT UPSC\r\nI MAY BE A DEADBODY WITHOUT THIS', 'DISCIPLINE, COURAGE, COMPETENCY, REGULARITY, AND TOP OF THAT STRONGLY HONEST SELF PREPARATION', 'LAST 3 ATTEMPT\r\nI HAVE NO OTHER OPTIONS AND WAYS\r\nSIR I HAVE TURNED MY REAL NEGATIONS INTO MY MOTIVATIONS', 'MY WILL POWER', 'POSITIVITY,\r\nREGULARITY,\r\nDISCIPLINED ROUTINED LIFE STYLE\r\nNEED A SUCCESS IN UPSC (DIE HEART) ASAP TO GAIN MY LOST CONFIDENCE BACK IN ME', 'FINANCE,\r\nLESS ATTEMPT (3 LEFT), \r\nCSAT,\r\nPSIR NOTES HOPE TO COPE PSIR UP SOON', 'CSAT(MATHS)\r\nLACK OF PROPER REVISIONS\r\nECONOMICS', 'DAILY 2 HOURS CSAT\r\nNEED A VEDIOW SERIES OF STRATEGIC MATHS CSAT SERIES\r\nMAKE A PROPER SCHEDULE TO COMPLETE 3 PROPER REVISION\r\nSOLVE PYQS\r\nNEED TO GO THROUGH NITIN SINGHANIA FOR ECONOMICS\r\nSOLVE CURRENT AFFAIRS NOTES FROMS ANSWERS\r\nAND CONTACT TO MAJID SIR WHEN GET STUCK ANYWHERE', 'LERANING AT ANY CONDITION\r\nCRISP NOTES MAKING', 'FINANCE TENSIONS\r\nCACOPHONOUS NEGHBOURS\r\nLESS TIME REMAINING AT HAND FEAR\r\nNO ASURED PLAN B\r\nYOUTUBE (SOMETIMES)', 'FINANCE TENSIONS-SOL>CAARY ON WITH MY SCHOOLING AND PRIVATE TUITIONS SIMULTANEOUSLY PART TIME APROX 4 HRS 5DAYS\r\nCACOPHONOUS NEGHBOURS-> SOL>REBUYING AIR PLUGS\r\nLESS TIME REMAINING AT HAND FEAR->TRY TO GIVE MY BEST\r\nNO ASURED PLAN B>SOL>LET THIS ALMIGHTY DECIDE \r\nYOUTUBE (SOMETIMES) >SOL>WILL GO FOR POMODORO RULE', 'DISTRUCTIONS-\r\nFINANCE TENSIONS\r\nCACOPHONOUS NEGHBOURS\r\nSTRONG DISCIPLINE RESCHEDULE OF TIMINGS\r\nLESS TIME REMAINING AT HAND FEAR\r\nNO ASURED PLAN B\r\nYOUTUBE (SOMETIMES) WILL FIX THESE BY END OF THIS WEEK BRICK BY BRICK WITH SRATEGY ,PLAN, AND RESCHEDULING IN THREE DAYS  BY 25TH FEB 2025 11.50PM', '2025-02-22 21:52:14', '2025-02-22 21:52:14', NULL),
(80, 219, 'PCC2025141', 'Uplift status of my family in the society and help to uplift the vulnerable section of society especially through education.', 'Consistent hard work and right strategy.', 'Learning new things and understanding about society and my patents.', 'I think i am able to understand the need of exam a little bit.', 'Discipline and focus.', 'Distractions and financial issues. \r\nDistractions and financial issues.', 'Current affairs and time management.', 'Trying to get disciplined and to be more focused.', 'NO SPECIFIC STRATEGIES.', 'Mobile mainly and friends a bit.', 'Try to avoid using the mobile as much as i can.', 'Will try to overcome as soon as possible.', '2025-02-22 21:54:50', '2025-02-22 21:54:50', NULL),
(81, 167, '20252025', 'I aspire to become a civil servant to contribute meaningfully to society. Having observed my father’s dedicated service in the police force since childhood, I have been deeply inspired by his commitment to public welfare. Moreover, this role offers not only economic stability but also the opportunity to uphold a position of responsibility and respect within society.', 'The officer\'s aptitude, which I believe consists of honesty, discipline, and perseverance, is essential.', 'believe this job profile itself is a motivation. What can be more motivating than serving the nation and working for people? And since I have no Plan B, it motivates me even more to give my best and crack this exam by hook or by crook.', 'I believe that my discipline, my perseverance and my honesty toward myself are my greatest strengths.', 'I need to improve my time management skills because I often become so deeply engrossed in a task that I lose track of time. Additionally, my main challenge is maintaining continuity in my work, which is an area I need to improve.', 'Since my passion is street photography, and I am an internationally acclaimed street photographer, it consumes a significant amount of my time. I find it difficult to step away from this passion, which often diverts my focus and attention from my work and ultimate goal.', 'y main challenge is anxiety. As the exam approaches, my anxiety continues to increase, and I am struggling to overcome it.', 'To address this, I have incorporated walking and yoga into my study schedule. For the past three months, I have dedicated my mornings to yoga, pranayama, and walking to help keep my anxiety under control.', 'I don\'t have any major challenges, as I have no distractions or commitments holding me back. I am not in a relationship and have fully dedicated myself to my preparation. My only challenges are anxiety and my weaker subjects. To manage anxiety, I have incorporated yoga into my routine, and I plan to strengthen my weak subjects through more focused revision.', '1. My Passion - photography\r\n2. My habit of excessive reading\r\n3. My love towards sports\r\nI am unable to find more.', 'I have let go of these habits and fully focused on my preparation.', 'I have already worked on eliminating my distractions and have now completely isolated myself to focus on my Prelims preparation. I hope that these distractions will not bother me in the next three months.', '2025-02-22 21:56:04', '2025-02-22 21:56:04', NULL),
