(88, 87, '20251008', 'Job satisfaction, academic exercise, intellectual satisfaction, Career progress, Creating impact', 'Curiosity and interest in the subjects, consistency, discipline, humanities bent of mind.', 'To demonstrate my capabilities to myself, Crack this in my first attempt', 'My curiosity and interest, my humanities bent of mind, my answer writing skill, peripheral knowledge, consistency and discipline', 'physical and mental health', NULL, 'time management, lack of knowledge base as it is my first attempt so I haven\'t been able to assimilate the standard materials of some subjects.', 'Following the exam schedule I will try to revise more and more.', 'For the last 28 days, I will not burden myself with over-information, rather I am going to have a targeted approach. I am making some Quick Revision Notes, and consolidated some online materials such as explanations of SNTCSSC\'s mock tests and some other materials.', 'Nothing like that', 'Not Applicable', 'Not applicable', '2025-02-22 23:00:59', '2025-02-22 23:00:59', NULL),
(89, 202, '20252076', 'Positive Impact on the Society and an opportunity to serve the nation from close quarters.', 'Perseverance, Patience, Open-minded, Curiosity, Hard Work and Smart Work (like maps and diagrams, Difference charts), and Emotional Intelligence.', 'To be able to crack the exams.', 'Capacity to work hard, patience and curiosity.', 'I believe that I should also acquire regular reading habits of books beyond the syllabus as I have mentioned reading as one of my hobbies in DAF. I\'m struggling to inculcate the daily reading goals. I also believe I need to work on my essay writing skills and short hand writing skills for mains (like ready made notes of the toppers).', 'CSAT and Art and Culture might be a hurdle in the prelims section.', 'Regular Revison of basic concepts and their application, CSAT are my  hurdle and including my weaker subjects that have been previously mentioned. I believe if the themes and the micro themes for the upsc papers and other exams conducted by UPSC would be handy. Sometimes, CAs are given from a long date back as well, so, I believe that is a problem. I am also in a dilemma if I should allocate more time to the art and culture and science and technology as these are not low hanging fruits and not high yielding marks subjects and mostly uncertain in nature. I also have difficult in memorising facts and more comfortable with the concepts.', 'Regular Mock Tests conducted \r\nI believe at least 3-4 revisions in my strong subjects and 6-7 revisions for my weaker areas. Regular CSAT Practice.', '1. Practice CSAT Section Wise and Solving PYQs. \r\n2. Allocating more time to the weaker subjects like art and culture.', '1. New CAs attract unnecessary attention sometimes. (Dopamine Effect). \r\n2. CSAT; I have had mathematics till class 10th level only, so there\'s a fear factor associated with maths.', 'A. Through guidance at SNTCSSC \r\nB. Practice \r\nC. Follow the microthemes and macro theme more closely.', 'By the end of March, I should have grip over my weaker subjects. And I aim to have at least 6-7 average revisions for every subject before Prelims.', '2025-02-22 23:01:51', '2025-02-22 23:01:51', NULL),
(90, 125, '20251065', 'The idea of a career in the Civil Services has been with me since the last 10 years of my life undyingly, chiefly because of the diversity and avenues offered, the soft and hard skillset it promises to teach and above all giving me the type of job satisfaction I have gradually understood to want given its public oriented work avenues.', 'Values required: Honesty, Principles, Determination and Integrity\r\nHabits Required: Consistency, Positive Approach, Self evaluation, Constant analysis, Open mind and Countering fatigue', 'My vision of achieving my desired service of the IFS and making my small contribution towards Making India Great Again in the world forum.', 'Clarity of vision and a goal; determination; positive attitude, honesty and integrity towards the preparation.', 'Time management, completing schedule completely and not only 90%, tackling distractions in a better manner.', 'Lack of adequate revisions, stress affecting presence of mind, unfortunate logistical problems', '1. Knowledge gap, as it is my first attempt\r\n2. Not adequate revisions\r\n3. Making crisp and useful notes\r\n4. Handling current affairs and CSAT\r\n5. Difficulty in concentrating as the bulkiness of the syllabus keeps lingering in the back of the mind.', '1. Cover basic source materials comprehensibly and read explanations for covering basic knowledge gap\r\n2. Giving 2 hours per day for revisions\r\n3. Seek guidance for note making\r\n4. Practice CSAT daily on target basis, same for current affairs', '1. Cover basic source materials comprehensibly and read explanations for covering basic knowledge gap\r\n2. Giving 2 hours per day for revisions\r\n3. Seek guidance for note making\r\n4. Practice CSAT daily on target basis, same for current affairs\r\n5. Do self evaluation each day and correct mistakes', '1. Urge to check phone during studying\r\n2. Family commitments and distractions when at home\r\n3. Peers\r\n4. Social Media (occasionally)\r\n5. Urge to take frequent but long breaks', '1. Keeping phone away \r\n2. Studying more in the library\r\n3. Balancing interaction time better with peers\r\n4. Cutting off social media time completely  (Already started)\r\n5. Self control and using breaks as a reward', '1. Phone addition to be overcome gradually by each week, by reducing using time gradually to completely by March\r\n2. Family distractions to be overcome by spending more hours in the library (already achieved nearly)\r\n3. Peer driven distractions to be eliminated by mid March completely\r\n4. Social Media distraction already overcame\r\n5. Urge for bigger breaks to be brought down my March', '2025-02-22 23:02:52', '2025-02-22 23:02:52', NULL),
(91, 85, '20251006', 'IT WILL ENABLE ME TO PARTICIPATE DIRECTLY IN OFFICIAL WORK AND WELFARE OF CITIZENS. THE PREPARATION ITSELF HELPS IN BUILDING PERSONALITY AND VALUE INCULCATION AND KEEPS ME AWARE ABOUT THE CURRENT SITUTAION OF MY COUNTRY.', 'PERSEVERENCE, REMAINING HONEST WITH MY OWN PREPARATION, DISCIPLINE, SELF BELIEF.', 'MY DREAM AND MY PARENTS WHO ARE HELPING ME A LOT TO FULFILL MY DREAM', 'WILLPOWER, CONSTANT MOTIVATION FROM MY PARENTS', 'NERVE FAILURE IS THE MAJOR PROBLEM THAT I HAVE TO IMPROVE ANY HOW, HAVE TO OVERCOME MY LAZINESS A BIT MORE', 'MY IMPATIENT BEHAVIOUR AND LESS ADAPTIVE NATURE', 'LACK OF REVISION AND CLEARING CSAT IS CHALLENGING', 'HAVE TO INCREASE 1 MORE HOUR IN MY DAILY SCHEDULE AND GAVE 4 HOUR FOR CSAT', 'DOING MEDITATION DAILY, MAINTAING A DIARY WHRE I WRITE ABOUT MY WEAKNESSES AND SOLUTIONS THERE ONLY AND READ IT ONCE A DAY', 'SLEEP\r\nRESTLESSNESS', 'CONTINOUSLY TRYING TO TAME MY MIND THROGH PRODUCTIVE ACTIVITES', 'SLEEP :: 2 WEEKS\r\nRESTLESSNESS AND ANXIETY:: 1 MONTH', '2025-02-22 23:23:12', '2025-02-22 23:23:12', NULL),
