(94, 152, '20252004', 'For getting inner fulfillment,job satisfaction  and a better career to showcase my skills.', 'Maintaining Consistency, Determination, Disciplines and Practicing Smart study every day irrespective of anyone\'s mood. Getting effective guidance and mentorship is utmost necessary also now a days to crack this examination.', 'To conquer the goal for proving myself.', 'Reading is my hobby since childhood. Having a good academics(University Gold medalist in Bachelor\'s), qualifying multiple National level competitive examinations before like WBJEE, GATE etc with good rank I know how to strategize and analyze things,solving MCQs.. I can sit for long hours giving my all for it.', 'Sometimes I get over sensitive and over emotional which I need to check.', 'Anxiety, frequent thinking about earlier attempts and wasting time, Sleeplessness due to anxiety.', 'Anxiety, the fear of losing and self doubt.', 'Practicing Meditation, Pranayama, self talk, journaling etc.', 'Focus on Breathing and drinking water or chocolate whenever get anxious. \r\nPracticing more tests \r\nRevising more times,\r\nDoubt clearing', '1. Fear of Losing \r\n2. Overthinking about past attempts', 'Journaling\r\nWriting down each thought, each problem and its solution \r\nSelf counseling', 'Same as the above \r\nWithin 28.02.2025', '2025-02-22 23:48:08', '2025-02-22 23:48:08', NULL),
(95, 211, '20252090', 'As it gives me much strength and authority to change the Social, economic problem prevalent in the country. It utilises best of my personality to work for the needy and deserving people of the country. In no job other than UPSC , gives me opportunity to impact people and society in such drastic way. When I started my UPSC preparation, rather taking it as burden, I am enjoying it like playing a game as I am learning new things every time which enriches my capacity.  I have to return something to my society and Environment as a form of service/SEVA as from my childhood I consumed resources from my society and Environment', 'Consistency and discipline, Patience, Determination and perseverance', 'I am thinking that I have to do everything to crack this exam as I don’t have any PLAN B . I must be and I will be clearing this Exam by hook and crook . My mentality is - There is no other option and no way to reverse back', 'Determination and perseverance to clear this Exam by anyhow , Marathon like consistency, I don’t have any PLAN B and as a full time aspirant I devote maximum of my time and potential to prepare this exam', 'Overthinking problem in silly moments, giving lame excuses, Being a foodie person, I need to change and check my eating/food habits', 'Overthinking, Lack of consistency after continuous 10-12 hours study for 7-10 days then giving excuses to myself, lack of confidence due to low success rate of this exam', 'Procrastinating for revision and analysis of already given mock tests . Lack of consistency , overthinking', 'Self assessment and spending quality time to myself. Setting goals and executing them in reality.', 'After every failure or lack of consistency, I studied again like a fresh start.', 'Overthinking and self-control, Movies and tv shows watching, bad eating habits, After hard study for 7-10 days(for 10 hours/day) I crumble and relaxed for 2-3 days , it breaks that virtuous cycle thus filling me with anxiety and regret/self guilt so LACK OF CONSISTENCY , Too much intimacy and spending time with roommates in the hostel', 'I need to control my mind, self assessment and spending time with myself. Taking right decisions etc', 'I will change myself right from now, the very next moment', '2025-02-22 23:59:32', '2025-02-22 23:59:32', NULL),
