(122, 288, 'PCC2025065', 'There are certain factors which motivated me to choose civil service:\r\n1) I want to bring positive changes in governance, policy making and public service by serving the people\r\n2) It will provide me diverse opportunities to explore my career growth\r\n3) Job stability, power and respect', 'Values: Honesty, Integrity, Patience, Perseverance, self-confidence, Empathy\r\nHabits: Hardwork, Self-discipline, follow a daily routine, involve in a physical excercise for fitness', 'The smile I can bring on my mother\'s face and thousand of other people as an civil servant', 'Hardworking, Perseverance, empathy, honesty', 'I have low patience level, need to improve my focus, overcome my stress and anxiety, need to be less emotional, need to control my anger sometimes.', 'Poor time management skills, difficulty in retention and revision, mental stress and self-doubt, overthinking, lack of confidence, distraction from phone.', 'Poor time management, not able to complete daily targets in time, self doubt and anxiety, improper mock test analyse.', 'Increase my study times, do yoga and meditation daily, make a realistic routine, analyse the mock test performance daily, practise PYQs with revision.', 'Wake up early, Working on my weak areas, Practise mock test , Multiple revisions, Keep limited resources, daily practise pyqs, analyse test performance, do yoga regularly', 'Phone overuse, overthinking, self-doubt, Lack of motivation, societal pressure', 'Keep my phone outside while studying, Make a proper study plan, set daily achievable targets, daily yoga practise, multiple revision to gain confidence, counselling session, ignore the society.', 'Overuse of phone-5 days, overthinking and self doubt-2 weeks, Lack of motivation- 1 week, societal pressure- trying to overcome daily', '2025-02-23 19:14:03', '2025-02-23 19:14:03', NULL),
