(130, 287, 'PCC2025130', 'I want to prepare for Civil Services because I am deeply committed to serving the public and making a meaningful impact in my community. I believe that through civil services, I can contribute to policy making that addresses critical issues such as education, healthcare and poverty alleviation. The opportunity to work on diverse challenges and lead initiatives that improve the lives of citizens is incredibly motivating for me.', 'According to me, Discipline, Time management, Persistence and Patience, Positive Attitude , Mental and Physical Health, self motivation, adaptability are essential for topping the Civil Services Examination.', 'The preparation process itself is a journey of self improvement. It helps me enhance my knowledge and develop critical thinking. Everyday of study brings me closer to not only clearing the exam but becoming a better version of myself.', 'When the journey feels long and tiring or facing tough moments , my persistence helps me stay focused on the final goal. Also I am reflective about my weakness and use them as stepping stones.', 'I can sometimes get so focused on studying that I neglect my physical well being. So I need to improve in making time for fitness routine. Secondly, though I can stick to a study schedule, there are times when I lose focus or let distraction take over . I need to improve in maintaining consistent effort throughout the entire preparation, ensuring that no day goes without meaningful progress.', 'Sometimes Social media interrupt my study sessions and reduce my productivity and focus. Secondly, sometimes negative people or negative comments makes me disappointed.', 'I\'m struggling with maintaining consistent focus during long study hours, managing the vast syllabus, and handling stress from the pressure to perform well. Balancing study time with personal life is also challenging, along with keeping up with current affairs regularly.', 'To tackle these challenges, I\'ll break the syllabus into manageable parts , set clear goals , use the Pomodoro technique, practice stress - relief methods, maintain a balanced routine , and dedicated specific for daily current affairs updates.', 'Creating a detailed study plan, prioritizing tasks, and sticking to a disciplined schedule. Using techniques like Pomodoro method to stay focused and minimize distraction. Meditation can be the key to managing stress.', 'Social Media, casual chats with friends, overthinking, over scheduling, unnecessary multitasking', 'According to my plan to overcome these distractions are prioritize tasks , set limits for social media and chats , practice mindfulness to reduce overthinking, avoid over scheduling focus on one task at a time and set clear boundaries and rewards for progress.', 'Social media - constantly checking and scrolling is the distraction . I need to start limiting social media to 30 minutes per day within 1 week. Gradually reduce usage over the next month.\r\nCasual chats with friends - losing focus by chatting during work is the distraction.. I need to set specific chat times during breaks and I should do flight mode to avoid unnecessary calls at study time.\r\nOverthinking - I need to start practicing mindfulness or journaling daily for 10 minutes with in 3-5 days.\r\nOver scheduling - review my daily study plan and keep the prioritizing tasks rather than unnecessary tasks.\r\nUnnecessary multitasking - I need to start immediately to focus on one task with the pomodoro Technique.', '2025-02-23 21:07:16', '2025-02-23 21:07:16', NULL),
