(135, 223, 'PCC2025159', 'I was in the Academics; pursuing PhD from IIT KGP (GATE AIR 280). Then I have qualified for several national level examinations like CSIR NET LS (AIR 73), DBT JRF, WBSET 2022, BARC PhD programs, ASRB NET etc. In 2022, my father was diagnosed with Osteosarcoma (a very rare type of Adult bone cancer), my world fell apart. I had to leave PhD (as my fellowship was not regular; treatment of cancer in India for middle class is next to impossible). I joined TATA Medical Cancer hospital, Rajarhat as a Research Assistant to support my family. In between we lost my father in 2023. Then I have started my preparation for competitive examinations as guided by my Therapist; It was my Father\'s wish to see me in a \"Central Govt Job\". I believe I have the ability to compete for Civil Services.So, resigned from the job and started full time preparation. With the Job demand and schedule, It was not possible to give the efforts as this exam demands.', 'Consistency, Patience, Determination, Courage to face the failure and get up once again. Most important to be disciplined.', 'I have sacrificed a lot till now; leaving the golden opportunity of completing my PhD after investing 5 long years. I do not want to live with this guilt that I had the time and opportunity (I am currently 29 years old), and I did not even try for it. I do not want to regret later on.', 'I am very much hard working, resilient, and positive person. I do not give up easily. I am very much obedient while taking advises from my mentors and follow them religiously. I maintain the consistency and do not take random breaks.', 'I need to build up my confidence more, increase focus/concentrations. Need to cut down the distractions.', 'Financial issues, limited number of attempts (only 3), Lack of proper guidance as I cannot afford luxurious coaching classes.', 'To cover the syllabus, utilize each day fully. Unable to cover the backlogs.', 'I have made a study plan along with daily routines, trying to increase my sitting time, I am doing asanas to improve concentration.', 'thinking of incorporating meditation in daily schedule.', 'Family problems, Financial issues, Health problems due to lack of nutritious food, scrolling whatsapp sometimes too much.', 'Reduced the phone uses, I am still figuring out how to cope up with the rests.', 'Will reduce the Whatsapp scrolling within this week.', '2025-02-23 22:18:44', '2025-02-23 22:18:44', NULL),
(136, 146, '20251098', 'The Civil Services Examination came to be known to me in my high school days, when I was thinking of planning for a career. I have always been sure of one thing, that is pursuing a profession wherein my individual efforts will have a positive impact on a lot many people. But I did not have a single profession that catered to my interests and goals. The nature of the Civil Services interested me because it is people oriented, requiring humane skills with a strong social standing. My further exposure to the understanding of the services in my educational and professional pursuits have only consolidated my interests making it inevitable for me to prepare for the same. I am also keen about learning new things, which makes this exam all the more lucrative for me.', 'The values of integrity and adaptability is foremost essential according to me. And in terms of habits- discipline, consistency and tenacity are important.', 'My mother and my small extended family who I am solely responsible for. To all of whom, my success will be as much theirs. Along with the fact that I do not have the liberty of six attempts due to my economic conditions at home.', 'I take UPSC CSE as my bird\'s eye goal, I am positively flexible i.e I do not get distracted or perturbed by changes and I am consistent. In terms of technical strengths- I have good grip over writing, fast reading and learning, and decent communication skills.', 'I need to work on my punctuality, patience and discipline in a few cases.', 'Family calamity as I have an active Stage 4 Cancer patient at home, and any dire economic need in the recent future.', 'Time constraints as I have started my prep quite late (September, 2024).', 'I have shifted my base to a relative\'s place in order to prevent getting affected by family circumstances, and trying to gradually increase study hours to cover the time I have missed out on.', 'I have made micro-plans as per daily schedules. I focus on completing my regular goals than thinking about macro goals frequently.  I have removed all of my social media access to prevent distractions. And I try to take one day at a time to overcome the overwhelm of the exam. I have monthly plans made, broken down into weekly and daily plans. This prevents anxiety and maintain flexibility as and when needed.', '1. My thoughts 2. YouTube Videos 3. Family invitations', '1. Meditation 2. Shifting to physical books over digital medium when the urge arises 3. Discuss with family', 'I wish to overcome my distractions before February ends.', '2025-02-23 23:22:51', '2025-02-23 23:22:51', NULL);
