(143, 251, 'PCC2025112', '1. Dynamic & diverse job profile what always induces me to embark on such challenging journey of preparation.\r\n2. Personal growth i.e critical thinking, bearing the weight, problem solving & communication etc.\r\n3. Job security is also one of the reason.', '•Disciplined daily life, \r\n•regular punctuality, \r\n•self assessment of daily study whether it exactly for the exam or not, \r\n•syllabus of personal life should be reduced as much as possible.\r\n•adoptive & diverse mindset.', '1. Personal satisfaction of self-improvement \r\n2. Strong desire of accomplishment \r\n3. Fear of regret i.e in upcoming days I don\'t want to regret of not giving my 100 %.\r\n4. Family support.', '1. confident about my foundational knowledge in my school days.\r\n2. I always prioritise my tasks to meet the deadline.\r\n3. Perseverance along with emotional intelligence to deal with procrastination and stay positive & flexible on daily basis.', '1. Need to be focused more \r\n2. Have to keep up with the regularity on daily basis(self-discipline)\r\n3. Mental well-being.', 'Mainly financial strain : family needs an earner.', '1. Actually I had backlog of more than 6 months since last year due to some reason ( mostly family problem). I\'m still suffering with those backlog alongside following the mock test series schedule.\r\n\r\n2. I\'m teaching in a home tuition twice a week (approx 7 hours/week, including journey) to pay my rent & other accomodation costs.', 'I have decided to leave some topics(in what I\'m not confident) to keep up with the preparation till this Prelims.\r\nAnd I need guidance regarding this.', 'I\'m prioritising the Mock Test schedule to revise & enrich my knowledge gap , what I have learned already. Alongside that I\'m trying to impose my backlog syllabus with the ongoing schedule.\r\nI need guidance regarding this.', '1. Mobile phone \r\n2. Listening too much music \r\n3. Part-time teaching in home tuition \r\n4. Financial strain \r\n5. Family stress', 'I have already overcome the mobile phone & music listening related distractions.\r\nI\'m trying to figure out the financial (related) distraction. Till now I can\'t see any solution.', 'The financial uncertainty appeared to me quite unprecedentedly & consequently, right now I don\'t have any exact idea how I\'m gonna resolve it.', '2025-02-24 00:51:03', '2025-02-24 00:51:03', NULL),
(144, 222, 'PCC2025237', 'I want to work with diverse sections of the society.', 'Consistency, hard work , discipline.', 'The chance that I have got to prepare for the examination.', 'Hard word.', 'Discipline.', 'Fear, anxiety.', 'Time management.', 'I have made a daily routine and everyday I try to follow it.', 'Currently I am following the test series schedule and have started revision.', 'Overthinking , tension , YouTube.', 'I have set a time limit for YouTube.', NULL, '2025-02-24 01:16:27', '2025-02-24 01:16:27', NULL),
(145, 43, 'OST2025217', 'I wanted a job where I could demonstrate my dedication towards public service. Civil service appealed to me for the meaning it creates in the life of public servants.', 'Patience, perseverance and the ability to deal with boredom as one has to revise the same things over and over again', 'The hope of seeing IAS beside my name', 'I don\'t give up easily and I am ready to work on my drawbacks', 'Sometimes I get too tired, I feel that needs to be conquered so that I have the enthusiasm to make each day fruitful', 'Laziness and procrastination', 'To revise the entire book at one go', 'I need to dedicate quality time and do mindful studying', 'Studying for short spans with repeated breaks to keep my mind fresh', 'Youtube, Sleep, Overthinking, lethargy, Random surfing on Google', 'I need to regulate my digital schedule strictly so that my sleeping time is well managed', 'Within February end I will get over them', '2025-02-24 01:22:15', '2025-02-24 01:22:15', NULL),
(146, 215, 'PCC2025265', 'It allows me to impact the lives of diverse sections of the society. It also helps me to grow personally and professionally.', 'right strategy,\r\ndiscipline ,consistency , self confidence', 'The reason why I have started preparing for this exam.', 'hard work and persistency', 'Discipline and consistency', 'Self confidence', '1.How to manage all the subjects\r\n2.Revisions', 'Following the test series schedule and alloted specific  time for revisions', NULL, 'Youtube, anxiety, over thinking', 'Walking and set time limit for youtube', NULL, '2025-02-24 01:34:46', '2025-02-24 01:34:46', NULL),
(147, 274, 'PCC2025103', 'I chose to prepare for the civil services because it offers a respectable position that allows me to work at the grassroots level, making a meaningful impact on people\'s lives. The opportunity to approach challenges from various levels of society excites me, and I believe that as a civil servant, I can contribute to shaping and building the framework of the country, fostering long-term development and progress.', '1. Discipline 2. Vision 3. Self Confidence 4. Time Management 5. Hard work 6. Smart work 7. Resilience 8. Mental health and stress management 9. To be ready for surprises (Adaptability and Flexibility) 10. Regular Revision with PYQ analysis', 'I\'ve experienced several ups and downs in life, and each failure, along with the resilience gained from it, motivates me every day. I have burned my bridges, and my sole focus now is to become an IAS officer.', '1. Resilience 2. Determination 3. Smart work 4. Clear Goal', 'I believe I could improve in a few areas, particularly time management, managing stress, and staying calm under pressure. These are areas that I’ve been actively working on through techniques like structured planning, mindfulness practices, and focusing on one task at a time.', '1. Stress and anxiety related to being a topper in my academics. 2. Struggles with knowledge gaps in certain subjects. 3. Difficulty concentrating, fearing I might miss out on other topics due to the vast syllabus and limited time.', '1. Strengthen subject knowledge and complete revision. 2. Improve time management in approaching questions. 3. Allocate dedicated study time, as my notice period at work ends on March 19th.', '1. Revise extensively and focus on difficult areas. 2. Take more mock tests to improve the number of questions attempted in 2 hours. 3. Once fully relieved from my job, I’ll be able to dedicate more time without distractions.', '1. Effective planning and execution. 2. Following the SFG schedule, dedicating time to read and revise test subjects. 3. Managing stress by completely detaching from social media.', '1. I am 30 years old and belong to the General category. So far, I have attempted the exam 3 times, but in the first two attempts, I wasn\'t adequately prepared. Since June of last year, after giving the Prelims, I have committed myself fully to my preparation. However, I only have 2 attempts left before I turn 32. The delay in my preparation wasn’t due to a lack of seriousness, but rather due to unforeseen personal challenges that took years to overcome. My biggest fear and distraction now is the possibility of failing. 2. Work pressure limits focus and study time on weekdays. 3. Anxiety and stress. 4. Lifestyle management. 5. Financial management.', '1. Meditate to manage anxiety. 2. Checking PYQs to ensure relevance in studies. 3. Dedicate weekends for revision, study, and exams on Sundays. 4. Practice Yoga. 5. Stay focused by keeping my phone off and using only the laptop for studying.', '1. I’m anxious about not revising the syllabus thoroughly, but I aim to complete 70% by March end. 2. Following Majid Sir\'s analogy, I’ve learned to control anxiety like a fire, it can destroy everything if uncontrolled, but if managed, it can be used constructively, like in cooking. I am trying to stay calm under pressure and focus on one step at a time, which has become a habit.', '2025-02-24 02:09:48', '2025-02-24 02:09:48', NULL),
(148, 196, '20252067', 'My parents dream to see me successful', 'Dedication \r\nMemory retention \r\nDiscipline about the grind and monotony', 'The fact that a secure job and stable future would be in store', 'I think I\'m not afraid of monotony \r\nAnd I\'m patient enough to persevere as evident from my previous failures', 'Social skills\r\nI\'m quite reticent and tend to avoid rather than ignore people', 'My exam jitters\r\nI have tendency to think both these options are right\r\nAlso too quick to mark', 'Time management \r\nToo many things to revise\r\nToo little time', 'Follow your guidance hopefully', 'Try my best to calm down', 'Instagram doomscrolling \r\nThat\'s the only one', 'I have a timer that limits my access to instagram after a certain set time', NULL, '2025-02-24 02:32:53', '2025-02-24 02:32:53', NULL),
