(153, 172, '20252031', 'It\'s my dream to join civil services.', 'Discipline & Consistency', 'My present situation', 'Myself', 'Need some improvement on discipline', 'My medium is Bengali. So, sometime I feel that it will be difficult. However nowadays it is not a major issue.', 'Shortcomings of time, some subject does not complete properly.', 'Give extra time to incomplete subjects, strictly follow the daily schedule', 'Daily schedule, avoid distraction.', 'Mobile', 'Avoid distraction', 'Within a week', '2025-02-24 09:50:46', '2025-02-24 09:50:46', NULL),
(154, 183, '20252043', 'Better opportunity & service condition and salary, dynamism of the service', 'Consistency, discipline,good mental and physical health , commitment to study', 'The prestige,respect and service condition of this esteemed institution & better opportunities to prove myself', 'Commitment and determination, grasping the essence of the exam', 'Sometimes, i overthink and get stressed unnecessary which affects my studies.', 'Sometime there are lot of pressure at my office work and have to extend office hours which then,in turn,puts constraints on my study schedule,for example during duare sarkar programme office hours were like 9--5 and the camps were at fur flung areas ,it took a lot of time in coming and going also, it was very tiring and exhausting at the same time, I could only study for 3-4 hours, that stresses me a lot and gives me anxiety as I can\'t complete my study targets within time schedule.Things like this might hinder.', 'Time constraints, writing problems for mains', 'Trying to push myself more everyday. More revision .', 'Keep going and do everyday study and revision ,fear less', 'Office hazards \r\nSometime family problems', 'I keep telling myself don\'t think much and do your job , studies must not be stopped. Sometimes do a little bit of yoga and medicine.', NULL, '2025-02-24 10:16:20', '2025-02-24 10:16:20', NULL),
(155, 280, 'PCC2025078', 'Diverse fields of opportunity with which I can enhance my capabilities and the opportunity to make some real positive social impact', 'Discipline, Consistency, Positive mindset, Optimism', 'Improvements no matter how small they are', 'Optimism and positive attitude', 'Confidence, Alert & active mind', 'Any sudden incidents although I see it positively always', 'I\'m struggling with time, although I try to follow the schedule but I couldn\'t complete the syllabus entirely', 'I\'ll not enter into any completely new areas during the last moments before exam, before that I will try to cover as much as possible', 'I stick to the areas I\'ve completed reading and try to solve questions by applying that knowledge and common sense in the mocks', '1. Sudden chaos/talking loudly near my surroundings \r\n2. Triggering words \r\n3. Talking with people who may bring down my confidence \r\n4. Social media \r\n5. Thinking about any past unresolved issues', 'I try to keep my mind cool and calm by practicing yoga and mindfulness meditation. I write down every 2-3 days interval to release stored thoughts and emotions and bring back my focus by reminding myself some positive affirmations.', 'During last 2 months before the Prelims, I\'ll stop interacting with people who brings down my confidence, I\'ll avoid watching any content in social media which are distracting for me and I\'ll talk to my parents to keep my surrounding peaceful as much as they can during that time.', '2025-02-24 10:18:01', '2025-02-24 10:18:01', NULL),
