(221, 179, '20252038', 'Because it is a great opportunity, allows a chance to contribute in the broader changes taking place in the society and the challenges that comes with the job constantly shapes human perspectives and outlook about self and world around. In short, it is a constant learning experience.', 'Learning from your mistakes, consistently working on them and advancing forward.', 'The fact that failure can never do justice to my efforts in a way that success will.', 'I have strong analytical capabilities and also capable enough in expressing them.', 'I struggle a lot in prioritizing subjects as per their weightage. This partly comes from my indecisiveness and lack of appropriate guidance.', 'I just need to add more hours to the preparation and overcome my lack of self-confidence.', 'So far, the only problem I am facing is preparing quality notes for the revision. Also, I would have appreciated if someone could have guided me for my optional subject.', 'I am limiting the sources so that my revisions are effective.', NULL, 'Mobile Phone and family exigencies.', 'I am working on these.', 'I am doing that for sure.', '2025-02-24 20:05:29', '2025-02-24 20:05:29', NULL),
(222, 15, 'OST2025122', 'AFTER INTROSPECTING MYSELF PROPERLY I REALISED THAT I HAVE SOME ASPECTS IN MY PERSONALITY LIKE LEADERSHIP QUALITY, IMPECCABLE OBSERVATION SKILL AND EMOTIONAL INTELLIGENCE WHICH CAN NO DOUBT MAKE A PERSON A COMPETENT CIVIL SERVANT.  MOREOVER  I GREW UP SURROUNDED BY INEQUALITIES WHICH ALWAYS TRIGGER ME TO CREATE SOME POSITIVE TRANSFORMATION IN PEOPLE\'S LIFE AND ADMINISTRATIVE MACHINARY CAN BE A GREAT TOOL TO ACHIEVE MY PURPOSE.', '1. CONTROL OVER ONE\'S EMOTION.\r\n2. PERSEVERANCE\r\n3. CRYSTAL CLEAR VISION \r\n4. BEING HONEST TO ONE\'S OWN SELF', 'THAT \"I\" INSIDE ME WHO MADE ME REALISE ONE DAY THAT I HAVE IMMENSE POTENTIAL WHICH IS YET TO BE USED.', '1. PERSEVERANCE\r\n2. BEING HONEST TO MY OWN SELF', 'MUCH MORE CONTROL OVER MY EMOTIONS', 'ANXIETY NOTHING ELSE ( EXCEPT ANY UNFORSEEN TRAGEDY)', 'THIS IS THE BEST ATTEMPT THAT I AM GOING TO GIVE. RIGHT NOW ANXIETY TO SOME EXTENT AND LATE NIGHT SLEEP ARE THE ONLY CHALLENGES TO ME.', '1. MY RECENT OBSERVATION IS TELLING ME THAT INCRESING CONFIDENCE IS DIRECTLY PROPORTIONAL TO DECREASING ANXIETY. AFTER MULTIPLE REVISIONS I AM SURE ANXIETY WILL GO DOWN TO A LARGE EXTENT. \r\n2. WORKING ON MY SLEEP CYCLE. I HAVE THREE MONTHS AHEAD WHICH IS MORE THAN ENOUGH TO CHANGE IT.\r\n2.', '1. DAILY EXERCISE (15-20 MINUTES CARDIO)\r\n2. PRACTICING MINDFULNESS AND POSITIVE SELF TALK FOR SOME TIME IN A DAY', '1. ANY KIND OF ARGUMENT \r\n2. FEAR OF FAILURE\r\nNOTHING ELSE', 'AS PER MY UNDERSTANDING DEEP BREATHING AND POSITIVE SELF TALK ARE THE ONLY WAYS TO HANDLE THESE.', 'EACH AND EVERY MORNING IS A NEW OPPORTUNITY TO ME. SO WITHOUT SETTING ANY TIMELINE I AM WORKING ON MY PROBLEM THEN AND THERE AND TRYING TO SOLVE IT.', '2025-02-24 20:13:30', '2025-02-24 20:13:30', NULL),
(223, 22, 'OST2025075', 'I want to take a direct part in the country\'s administration and have a dynamic work area.', 'Discipline, dedication, hardwork, patience and stress management.', 'I remember and write down the reason for giving this exam, I do daily affirmations.', 'I am hardworking and patient. I also value discipline and try to maintain it.', 'I sometimes tend to procrastinate. Also I get anxious during exam', 'Procrastination and exam time stress', 'Lacking a proper direction on how to revise, how analyze pyq and mock tests and how to make notes', 'This program has helped me in overcoming these obstacles to a good extent and I will regularly follow the program', 'I have started to revise daily, I analyse the tests according to the parameters.', 'Social media, youtube, webseries', 'Switching off smart phone while studying.', 'By the end of March I will remove all the distractions.', '2025-02-24 20:15:33', '2025-02-24 20:15:33', NULL),
(224, 23, 'OST2025071', 'As I belong to political science background this makes it easy for me to understand the administrative and political lacunas which we face in our every day Life. This makes civil services the most effective tool for me to address the loopholes and try to fix them which can only be possible once I become a part of this adminis trative machinery.', 'Consistency, hardwork and proper time management. \r\nThe will of \' Never to Give up\' perfectly fits here to be a quality to top this exam.', 'The very aim I see myself as an officer.', 'The very zeal of Never Giving up and the ability to analyse at the back of my mind about the mistakes that I commit while doing the preparation.', 'I want to shed away the one of the worst habits of my life or personality where I need an improvement are the bad qualities of Laziness and Procrastination.', 'Laziness, Procrastination & Lack of effective time management.', 'Seeing so much content I always face a FOMO and even if I revise I feel that the preparation is not going on a right track as I am not able to chalkout a Proper strategy for revision.', 'I can overcome these challenges with proper mentoring and guidance where I can strategise myself for the upcoming prelims and later were Mains exam.', '1. Restrict screen timing by setting usage time for particular apps to avoid screen distraction.\r\n2. Dedicate most of the time studying.', '1. Screen Distraction\r\n2. Mind deviation to other things then studies. \r\n3. Postponing things for later. \r\n4. Excessive sleep\r\n5. Laziness', 'For overcoming these distractions I plan to to do these things.\r\n1. Restrict usage of Mobile or any other screen. \r\n2. Focus more on studies.\r\n3. Try to be time specific.\r\n4. Take only required sleep\r\n5. Try to be more active and action-oriented towards studies.', 'In the next 3 months I am gone a focus specifically on prelims and will overcome my biggest demerits of Laziness and Procrastination by studying more.\r\n1. March- Prepare according to the syllabus and will try to complete the pending subjects.\r\n2. April- Revision along with PYQ\'s\r\n3. May- Only Mock test and try to solve as much previous year question papers of both GS and CSAT.', '2025-02-24 20:21:12', '2025-02-24 20:21:12', NULL),
