(228, 218, 'PCC2025059', 'Its dynamic nature.  Authority to do something for the country and its people. Can have the first hand avenue actually how the government/system runs/works.', 'Discipline, Hard work clubbed with smart work, Perseverance, Reading habit, Writing skills, Sincerity, Concentration', 'To get the job as early as possible', 'Grasping the matters in short time', 'What I have already written in the \'values and habits for topping this exam\' section', 'Firstly myself. Secondly there are other reasons of my family and my environment', 'That I have already mentioned in the \'values and habits\'. Parallelly  I\'m also preparing for the CHC mains', 'Studying by dividing time considering priority', 'Stared modifying my routine', 'Smart Phone, Reading irrelevant articles, Watching documentaries, Confusion, Over thinking', 'Carefully eliminating them by talking right decisions and choosing to do the work in accordance to my prioirty', 'almost 1 month or maybe more', '2025-02-24 20:36:13', '2025-02-24 20:36:13', NULL),
(229, 98, '20251020', 'I CHOOSE CIVIL SERVICE AS MY CAREER AS AN OPPOTUNITY TO ACHIEVE MY LIFE PURPOSE. IT\'S NOT ACTUALLY CONFINED TO GET A PRESTIGIOUS JOBS LIKE IAS, IPS OR ANYTHING ELSE , IT IS BEYOND OF THAT AS PER MY KNOWLEDGE BUT YES UPSC IS ONE OF THE MOST SOLUABLE AND I CAN SAY IT IS THE BEST OPTION TO TOUCH MY ASPIRATIONS FOR SERVE THE NATION, TO UPLIFT THE BACKWARDS (FROM WHERE I AM SPENDING MY LIFE), TO BRING THE SOCIAL CHANGE BY TAKLING CORRUPTION AND TO PROMOTING THE BASIC AMENITIES OF THE COMMON MASSES.', '1. DISCIPLINE, 2. CURIOSITY OF SEARCHING KNOWLEDGE, 3. HONESTY IN YOUR STUDY AND TO MANAGE YOUR TIME TABLE, 4. HARDWORK, 5. DEDICATION, 6. BE SIMPLE, 7. MAINTAINING HEALTHY FOOD HABBITS, 8.PEACE OF MIND OF SELF SATISFECTION AND SELF CONFIDENCE WHAT ACTUALLY MOTIVATES YOU TO PUSH YOURSELF BEYOND THE BOUNDARY OF YOUR LIMITATIONS.', 'TO CHANGE WITHIN MYSELF AND THAT WHAT FURTHER MOTIVATES ME TO CHANGE IN THE SOCIETY.', 'MY SLEF CONFIDENCE AND MY DEDICATION AND ONE OF THE BEST TO SAY MY BACKGROUNDS FROM WHERE I CAME TO HERE TO PREPARE FOR FUTURE CHANGE WITH A LITTLE BIT OF HOPE THAT IS MY OPTIMISTIC STRENGTH FOR STANDING AT THE BELOW ZERO LEVEL TO CRACK THE INDIA\'S ONE OF THE TOUGHEST EXAMINATION.', 'NOONE IS PERFECT SO IN THAT WAY I CAN SAY THAT I SHOULD CHNAGE MY SELF ACCORDING TO THE NATURE OF THE EVERY SITUATIONS SOMETIMES ROUGH SOMETIMES I NEED TO BE TOUGH. AND I AM NOT WANT TO BE A EGOISTIC PERSON,SO I CAN CHANGE MY EGO IN RESPECT OF MY EVERY SUCCESS OF MY LIFE.', 'THE MOST BASIC AND THE MOST PROMINENT IS FINANCIAL PROBLEMS. DUE TO LACK OF PROPER FINANCIAL HELP MOST OF THE TIMES I NEED TO THINK ABOUT MY NEXT BEST MINIMUM OR OPTIMUM ALTERNATIVE MEALS OF THE DAY, & DUE TO THIS SOMETIME I CHOOSE TO STAY HUNGRY. AND ALSO I GOT DISTURB BY MY SURROUNDINGS WITHOUT ANY REASONS IT IS HAMPERING MY STUDIES A LOT.', 'RIGHT NOW LACK OF PROPER REVISION.', 'I PLANNED MY CHALLENGES ACCORDING TO THE SFG SCHEDULE. I WILL FOLLOW SFG ROUTINE PROPERLY.', 'PROPER REVISION, NOT TO INCLUDE NEW ADDTIONAL BURDEN OF NOTES, LESS STUDY MORE REVISION AND TO FOLLW SFG SCHEDULE  SPECIALLY MOCK TESTS.', '1. SELF EGO, 2. SOMETIMES BREAKING THE DAILY SCHEDULE, 3.YOUTUBE, 4. SPENDING MOST THE TIMES WITH FRIENDS TO TALKING UNNECESSARY THINGS, 5. SOMETIME I GOT TO EMOTIONAL ABOUT MY FUTURE, MY FAMILY AT THAT PEAK TIME I REALLY FEEL SAD AND IT IS HAMPERING MY STUDIES.', 'TO TAKING A HARSH DECISION, TO FACING THE CHALLENGES WHAT WOULD BE RESULT BUT I WILL FACE WITH MY COURAGE, I WILL DO WHATEVER I WANT TO DO TO CRACK THE CSE EXAMINATION IN MY COMING ATTEMPTS.', 'YES IDENTIFIED. I AM HOPING TO OVERCOME OF THESE DISTRUCTIONS.', '2025-02-24 20:36:56', '2025-02-24 20:36:56', NULL),
(230, 298, 'PCC2025118', 'Though there are many other jobs and services with handsome salaries but my decision to choose to prepare civil services is, to make a positive impact in the society to many dimensions. the honour, the pride which I am always aiming and dreaming in my daily life. Service to the Nation is always before making money. NATION FIRST ALWAYS FIRST.', 'Discipline, Never give up, work under tremendous pressure, loyal to the Nation and the society, service before self.', 'Want to be India\'s most Efficient Officer one day, wan to contribute to the journey of India\'s aim to be \"VISHWAGURU\".', 'Never give up mentality, proactive, loyal to my work to clearing this exam.', 'I want to be more disciplined.', 'Nervousness.', 'Consolidation of resources.', 'Limited resources, meditation, exercise, spirituality.', 'Controlled restrictions on myself regarding interaction with the world.', '1. People. \r\n2. Events.', 'Controlled restrictions on myself.', '2 months from now.', '2025-02-24 20:40:40', '2025-02-24 20:40:40', NULL),
(231, 205, '20252081', 'To serve for the needy and deserving people of my country and UPSC gives me opportunity to impact people and society.', 'Discipline, consistency,  perseverance', 'As it is one of the toughest exams in India, I feel that I have the guts to clear it and I will clear the exam.', 'Determination, consistency', 'Overthinking, a bit of nervousness.', 'Overthinking,  nervousness.', 'Lack of consistency.', 'Self assessment. Setting the goals and execute them in alloted time.', 'Start the day with lots of positive energy ,setting the goals and execute them.', 'Overthinking,  nervousness, junk food addiction, oversleeping, social media addiction.', 'I need to control myself from doing these distractions, self assessment.', 'I am trying my best to overcome the distractions and I will succeed.', '2025-02-24 20:44:30', '2025-02-24 20:44:30', NULL),
(232, 303, 'PCC2025246', 'This exam is highly prestigious and competetive and clearing this exam is a remarkable achievement,it gives us the opportunity to serve our country and this is one of the best carrier option too.', 'Discipline,perseverance,effective time management,staying motivated', 'A desire to feel accomplished and proud,support and encouragement from my family members', 'As i am always a sincere student from school time i have a solid grasp in fundamental concepts in subjects like geography history polity etc and as i have completed my graduation in English i have proficiency in vocabulary and grammar also', 'I need to be consistent and cut down the negative thoughts', 'Lack of consistency', 'Easily get demotivated and due to scarcity of time can\'t complete the whole syllabus of some subjects', 'Increase the study hours and doing exercises as told by mazid sir', 'Increase the study hours and by doing meditation and yoga', 'Social media\r\nYouTube reels\r\nmental health issues \r\nmessaging', 'Reduce the phone time', 'Use phone not more than 30minutes a day', '2025-02-24 20:45:02', '2025-02-24 20:45:02', NULL),
(233, 242, 'PCC2025001', 'Civil services offer a unique platform to implement policies and programs that can improve lives, whether it’s through education, healthcare, or infrastructure development. I always had a knack towards administration and management of programmes. However in high school I developed an inclination towards international relations and diplomacy. As I feel we need concrete restructuring of our external affairs policies and in IFS ro uphold the strength of India in the global stage, which motivates me further to join the civil service.', 'Dedication, Perseverance, Patience', 'Condition of my state and my country, my love for diplomacy as I want to become an IFS officer', 'Ability to mug up facts, understanding demand of the question and frame answer accordingly, good writing skill, I am from humanities background so most of the subjects are aligned to my familiarity, visualizing preparation management', 'Need to increase my Patience, need to stand firm on my ground and decisions, think consciously and judiciously with logic, complete tasks within deadline, not to get exhausted easily,', 'Fatigue, lethargy, daydreaming, being too harsh on myself', 'Even after reading and revising multiple times I still feel some topics are left behind, lack of handwritten notes for value addition, lack of short notes, revision of CA from Hindu, Maths portion from Csat', 'Preparing continuous short notes on diverse topics I come across, practising csat pyq daily,following YouTube channels for value added materials and analysis of topics but for CA revision from Hindu I don\'t have any strategy. The editorials and notes becomes too bulky for revision.', 'Currently I am following Sntcssc mentor\'s suggestion whole heartedly. I have prepared routine for revision, csat, mock test explanation and for static subjects for my daily schedule. I am reading philosophical books to motivate myself besides they\'ll help me for essay also. I have started listening audio books on upsc topics during my spare time and when travelling.', 'Daydreaming, Fatigue due to stress and long term battle of upsc, underconfidence, health issues, impatience', 'Meditation and pranayam for increasing concentration and controlling patience, depending on medicines for health issues, mock tests have helped me in gaining confidence on the subjects but stress and fatigue is something which is pushing me back every year. I don\'t have any solutions for that. Parents encourage me to have free time but still that doesn\'t help.', NULL, '2025-02-24 20:45:17', '2025-02-24 20:45:17', NULL),
