(246, 231, 'PCC2025256', 'I chose to prepare for civil services to serve society, address social issues, and contribute to nation-building through effective governance. This career offers opportunities to implement policies for the betterment of people, especially the underprivileged, and provides a platform for continuous learning and personal growth', 'Discipline, consistency, and perseverance are key values required for success in the Civil Services Examination. A strong work ethic, time management, and a growth mindset help in overcoming challenges. Regular revision, critical thinking, and self-awareness also play a crucial role in effective preparation', 'My biggest motivation is my parents, who have always supported me through every challenge. Their sacrifices inspire me to work harder and achieve my goal. Additionally, my passion for serving society and making a meaningful impact through civil services keeps me focused and determined', 'My ability to stay focused and disciplined is my biggest strength. I am consistent in my study routine, adapt to challenges, and have a problem-solving mindset. Additionally, my analytical skills and dedication to continuous learning help me stay motivated throughout the preparation journey.', 'I need to improve my ability to handle stress and anxiety, especially before exams. Sometimes, I tend to overthink and doubt my preparation.', 'The biggest obstacles could be self-doubt, time management issues, and unexpected personal responsibilities. Also, maintaining consistent motivation over a long preparation period is challenging. However, I am committed to overcoming these challenges with proper planning and discipline.', 'Currently, I am facing challenges in balancing multiple subjects, managing time effectively, and staying mentally resilient. Additionally, I am facing health issues, and my parents are also unwell, which makes it challenging. To manage this, I maintain a flexible schedule, focus on my health, and stay mentally strong.', 'I plan to overcome these challenges by creating a structured study plan, breaking the syllabus into manageable parts, and focusing on revision . I will also practice mindfulness and meditation to reduce stress and ensure I maintain a positive mindset throughout the journey', 'To tackle challenges and achieve my goals, I follow a structured study plan with revision, mock tests, and self-analysis.', 'Overthinking and self-doubt, Lack of a fixed sleep schedule ,External responsibilities and interruptions, Fear of failure and comparison with others, Social media and unnecessary screen time', 'BY maintaining a fixed study and sleep schedule, and practicing self-discipline .I am setting strict time limits for social media To manage self-doubt, I will focus on positive affirmations and avoid unnecessary comparisons with others. By Prioritizing my own tasks will help me stay on track,', NULL, '2025-02-24 21:32:03', '2025-02-24 21:32:03', NULL),
