(248, 101, '20251025', 'For job satisfaction and security along with wanting to be able to exercise influence and significant impact in administration and policy making in a way that contributes to the betterment of people at large and take pride in serving for the nation.', 'Discipline, Resilience, Consistency and Determination along with streamlined approach that yields the best results.', 'Visualising the end goal and be able to make my family proud and represent my community at a larger scale.', 'I’m driven and determined enough to devote the time and energy required to crack the exam.\r\nI’m well acquainted with the demands of the exam by now and am able to do so in a time bound manner.\r\nI’ve the required analytical and problem solving skills.\r\nI’m always eager to learn new things and am constantly trying to improve in whichever way required in order to ace.', 'I need to be more disciplined and learn to adhere to routines.\r\nI’ve to learn to be more assertive and confident and incorporate more self reflection.\r\nI need to learn to focus and how to sustain a prolonged interest and focus on the specific goal that I’ve chosen.', 'Procrastination, bad time management, and not being able to sustain interest and focus on one thing for long periods of time.', 'Lack of ample revisions to recall the specifics, often being overwhelmed with too much information, and hence, not being able to maximise accuracy level in the MCQs.', 'Try to revise especially the core subjects as many times as possible.\r\nLimit resources and focus on the important and repeated themes and micro themes, in order to not get overwhelmed.\r\nIdentify the mistakes made while attempting the questions and rectify them by taking more tests. \r\nTry to have a practical approach, manage time efficiently and cultivate an overall positive outlook so that I am able to enjoy the process instead of dreading it.', 'As mentioned earlier, I’ve narrowed down on resources, identified the weak areas to work 