(274, 228, 'PCC2025054', 'First of all, Desire for Public Service, then Prestige and Respect, Job Security, Diverse Career Opportunities, Power and Authority, Intellectual Challenge and many more.', 'Values should be - Discipline and Consistency, Perseverance, Integrity and Honesty, Curiosity and Open-mindedness, Self-motivation,\r\nAnd Habits should be - Smart Planning and Time Management, Active Note-making, Newspaper Reading, Answer Writing Practices, Mock Tests and Self-evaluation, Balanced Lifestyle, Staying Away from Negativity,', 'Strong \'WHY\' behind this preparation ( A clear GOAL), Fear of Regret, Role models and success stories, A Sense of Responsibility, Small Wins and Daily Progress, Fear of Competition, Self-Discipline over Motivation.', 'Strong work ethic & consistency, Analytical & critical thinking, Effective time management, Strong writing and articulation skills, adaptability and open mindedness, ability to learn from mistakes, interest in governance and current affairs, emotional resilience and patience', 'Procrastination and distractions, writing speed, revision techniques, stress management, prioritization, confidence and speaking skills (for interview)', 'Information overloaded and poor revision, procrastination and distractions, stress, anxiety and self doubt, uncertainty in prelims, writing speed, interview pressure and confidence issue', 'balancing current affairs and static syllabus, retention and revision issue, prelims uncertainty, optional subject managing, answer writing practices, maintaining motivation and avoiding burnout', 'I am focusing on giving more mock tests, analyzing the PYQs, daily studying current affairs, making concise notes repeated themes and micro themes wise to revise, daily MCQs practice.', 'Structured study plan, effective note making, revision strategies, prelims oriented strategy, current affairs mastery, mock test strategy, stress management and motivation', 'social media and smart-phones, overconsumption of study material, negative thoughts and self doubt, procrastination and laziness, social obligations and unnecessary conversations', 'Fixing the social media using time, keeping my phone switch off during the study time, I am following a strict booklist(NCERT books+ 1 standard book for each subject +2 monthly magazines for Current Affairs), I am keeping a daily progress journal, give myself targets and achieve that within the prescribed time, I am now very much avoiding any family / social interaction as I feel it wastes my study time.', 'social media and smart-phones - I am working on it and fixing it.\r\noverconsumption of study material - I am very much now according to the syllabus and following a strict booklist\r\n negative thoughts and self doubt - Ongoing\r\nprocrastination and laziness - Trying to fix it, hope will fix it very soon\r\n social obligations and unnecessary conversations - Ongoing', '2025-02-25 00:06:57', '2025-02-25 00:06:57', NULL),
(275, 220, 'PCC2025191', 'In beginning some toppers interview encouraged me. Then I think to change something I have to have that capability and power. UPSC can be that source of capacity to change others Lifes and become changed myself.\r\nSecondly, Civil service has the most diverse field area to work upon and it will give me such a broad and micro exposure to society and governance.', '1) Proper sources, strategy, guidance\r\n2) Enough practice and analysis\r\n3) Dedication, patience, perseverance, effective utilization of time, leadership qualities\r\n4) Holistic knowledge and perspective in any matter, subject or issues. Analytical thinking\r\n5) Understanding the root of any issues and finding most effective way to overcome that', '1) Very first and foremost, UPSC CSE was totally my own decision.\r\n2) I have nothing to lose now, all that can be happen to me is that I gain something.\r\n3) It is one of the most effective way to change my own life, my family and the society where I\'m living or working.', '1) Finding, Accepting and Working on my faults.\r\n2) Genuine and positivistic motive.\r\n3) I have a great quality of small and forward thinking and action', '1) Need continuous guidance because I lack direction\r\n2) Need to change the attitude of doing things at last point of time\r\n3) Laziness', '1) Laziness, and attitude of completing that activity at last point of time.\r\n2) Not taking proper and enough actions as per my own plans.', '1) Lack of revision\r\n2) Messing things up and feeling exhausted\r\n3) Taking longer time to solve a question than any other serios candidates\r\n4) Family pressure', '1) Start revising as per mock schedule\r\n2) Trying to study one subject during a week-long, and trying to keep things organized\r\n3) still having no plan\r\n4) Try to ignore family issues and pressure as much as possible', '1) Started revising as per mock schedule. still facing shortage of time to complete the whole one subject in a week\r\n2) Try to ignore family issues and pressure as much as possible but that does not works always', '1) Social Media\r\n2) Family\r\n3) Laziness\r\n4) overthinking\r\n5) Financial Condition', '1) Select a specific time period or breaktime to use social media\r\n2) Try to ignore family issues and pressure as much as possible\r\n3) Have enough sleep, proper diet, water and sunlight, Yoga\r\n4) Yoga, Meditation. Positive or affirmative words for myself. avoiding unnecessary thinking\r\n5) Started giving tuition to school students and encourage them with my affirmative words', '1) Social Media - A week\r\n2) Family - Not sure\r\n3) Laziness - 3 weeks\r\n4) Overthinking - 10-15 days\r\n5) Financial Condition - not sure', '2025-02-25 00:15:26', '2025-02-25 00:15:26', NULL),
(276, 263, 'PCC2025243', 'I am satisfying to do this job. I want to become a civil servant.', 'Hard working,  dedication and patience.', 'I will do it . I can do it.', 'Patience.', 'Regularity maintaing ,  late rising, time management.', 'Time management', 'Proper revision', 'After giving mock tests, check the answers properly.', 'Time management', 'Late rising, regularity maintaing, time management, proper revision, stress control, keep quite  and hold temper.', 'Trying to improve my study timing.', 'Time management in proper way . I am trying to overcome it.', '2025-02-25 00:17:02', '2025-02-25 00:17:02', NULL),
(277, 143, '20251088', 'To find myself pursuing a higher calling in the fruits of service to one and all. Having worked in the corporate sector for a while, there was a need to discover more to life than just a barely aware social livelihood.', 'Discipline, regularity, focus, humour.', 'In spite of health challenges in the last 3 years, and loss of loved ones, the ultimate desire is to do better and be better. The motivation is to be as good as my father in being a true human being who finds satisfaction in his work.', 'Clear head, curiosity, willingness to fight back from tough situations.', 'Better demarcation of time, focused thinking, narrower strategies.', 'Family issues, self doubt at times when making unexpected mistakes.', 'Optional change took too much time to cover, and so could start with Prelims a little late. The mountain is steep to climb insofar as revising old material, but there\'s always new edges that keep coming out to the same texts.', 'Weekly plans broken down into daily targets; rewarding myself for looking at old material by a payoff every 2-3 days.', 'Using excel sheets to make daily plans, time regulation by app, waking up every day with 5-10 mins meditation, writing the material to be covered and a positive line every day on my own board.', 'Zoning out, catching up with friends, cinema, food, lack of movement.', 'Setting small targets and taking adequate short breaks, using timer clock, phone usage only for one hour at night, time usage regulated, daily 3 km walk.', 'The timeline is these next 2 months, perfecting the daily routine so as to approach the exam in a clear, precise, logical and freshly rested, less tense way. The brain and effort will take care of the rest.', '2025-02-25 00:20:35', '2025-02-25 00:20:35', NULL),
(278, 66, 'OST2025161', 'I realised that the knowledge of the syllabus will make me a man with higher thinking level and it will make me able to understand the system and It\'s a handsome carrier opportunity.', 'Consistency, enough willpower to crack the exam, mastering PYQ.', 'The feel that I will be very related to the administrative system and wish to having part of that. And feeling of understanding the system and the world in very much  better way and I will be able to takes things factually and not emotionally like maximum people in society..... If I clear the selection process for once .', 'Willpower and consistency.', 'Proper Planning and acting according to that plan strictly without mental disturbances.', 'Destruction of mobile and job related matter and some personal issues.', 'Mobile destruction,  work life life destruction and My sister chronic illness for long days .', 'Nowadays whenever I study , I keep mobile in my groud floor room and I study in my first floor room to be safe from.mobile destrution.\r\nFor work life I manage works with others colleague who do study so that I dont have to go office everyday .', 'Nowadays whenever I study , I keep mobile in my groud floor room and I study in my first floor room to be safe from.mobile destrution.\r\nFor work life I manage works with others colleague who do study so that I dont have to go office everyday .\r\nAnd I cant do anything for my sister chronic illness .. often she shouts and cry in pain and the I cant concentrate in study ... Fir 3 years she is suffering like that , recently she got appendix sergery after two days of sergery she again got admitted today for intense belly pain .', 'Mobile\r\nSister illness\r\nShouting in my house by mother regarding house related matter\r\nJob destruction \r\nPersonal', 'Keeping mobile in the far room while studying, \r\nClosing doors and windows for getting house related shoutings.\r\nPYQ discussions with a  sntcssc mate', 'Within one week  \r\nAnd if My sister gets well its will be great relief for me beacuse till appendix operation doctors cant diagnos properly for which thing she is suffering for exactly and after operation again she is getting pain.', '2025-02-25 00:26:19', '2025-02-25 00:26:19', NULL),
(279, 294, 'PCC2025007', 'After my post-graduation, I explored different career options and realized that Civil Services suited me best. It offers opportunities to learn, solve problems, and serve society while also providing respect and responsibility.\r\n\r\nMy interest in IFoS comes from my background in Botany and love for nature. The variety of job roles, leadership opportunities, and the chance to contribute to the country\'s development inspired me to choose this path.', 'To top the Civil Services Exam, need honesty, consistency, and a mix of hard work and smart work. Staying disciplined, learning from mistakes, and not giving up are very important. Success comes from continuous effort and the right strategy.', 'My current struggles, parents\' dreams, and the goal of achieving something big motivate me to give my best every day. I want to improve my life and make a meaningful impact.', 'Not giving up and learning from my mistakes.', 'I need to improve time management, procrastination, overthinking, stress, and good health.', 'Earlier, lack of guidance was a challenge, but I am lucky to have Majid Sir now.\r\nFinancial constraints and distractions from other job exams are also obstacles, but I remain focused.', 'Effective revision & Haphazard study approach.', 'I focus on covering and revising properly, following a structured study plan, and sticking to a schedule.', 'I follow a structured study plan, regular revision, and a fixed schedule. To manage stress, I practice exercise and meditation, while avoiding distractions and staying motivated.', '1. Other job exam preparations\r\n2. Overthinking and self-doubt\r\n3. Social media and unnecessary screen time\r\n4. Financial worries\r\n5. Lack of structured revision leading to a haphazard approach', '1.Prioritizing UPSC and limiting focus on other exams.\r\n2.Practicing meditation.\r\n3.Reducing screen time and using it only for study purposes.\r\n4. Managing expenses wisely and seeking affordable study resources.\r\n5.Following a structured study plan with regular revision.', 'I continuously work on my distractions, and some are ongoing. I hope to overcome them soon.', '2025-02-25 00:27:08', '2025-02-25 00:27:08', NULL),
(280, 235, 'PCC2025139', 'I want to serve society, and there are many ways to do so. However, becoming an IAS officer provides a secure platform and the authority to implement significant plans for the community. That\'s why I aspire to become a successful IAS officer and have started to prepare so .', 'Discipline and consistency', 'Internal drive', 'Consistency', 'Managing interruptions while studying and utilizing the daily routine effectively', 'Proper guidance from a mentor is important to ensure I\'m following the right path or not to clear Prelims , as this attempt really matters to me but I think I\'m lacking that support .', 'Too much to cover and recall but can\'t remember all the things I already have studied .', 'Not sure but may be through revisions .', 'By making proper plans and following it and being consistent.', 'Negetive thoughts', 'Not sure', 'Want to overcome as soon as possible and anyhow .', '2025-02-25 00:34:43', '2025-02-25 00:34:43', NULL),
(281, 305, 'PCC2025264', 'Along with a good career prospects there is enormous opportunity to serve my nation .', 'Integrity', 'My inner self', 'Discipline', 'Communication skill, self -awareness, emotional growth, social growth (openness)', 'Procrastination', 'Complete the syllabus', 'Studying and revising', 'A well desciplined plan', '1.endless screen time\r\n2.procastination\r\n3. Negative thoughts', '1. Stick to a schedule\r\n2.track my daily activities \r\n3.exercise and meditation \r\n4.keep electronics away \r\n5.put off the small things \r\n6.keep myself healthy and happy', 'Distraction - Uncertainty, fear \r\nThe only to get rid of a distraction is to purport mind there is no time. Today is the last day, Tomorrow is the exam.', '2025-02-25 00:42:17', '2025-02-25 00:42:17', NULL),
(282, 132, '20251070', '1.most prestigious government Job in India \r\n2. The possibility of creating a +ve change in society\r\n3. Desire to help the people, in the remotest corner of India ,  who really needs govt\'s support to grow.', 'Consistency , Discipline and hard work is neccessery but not suffiencient.I believe the most important value which helps to crack this exam is perseverence that is rising up after each failure.', 'My Parents , My God & My own inner calling.', 'My ability to learn any concept very quickly.', 'Staying right on track , or laser sharp focus , is what I think is needed.', 'None', 'Sometimes getting distracted by Phone', 'Using Forest App to increase productivity', 'Reward based strategy : after a slot of study 3 hrs , I give myself a long break', 'Phone , My thinking process,My extra curiosity , My Researching Habit', 'Using mindmaps , small notepads', 'By 25th March 2025 : All distraction will be brought under complete control', '2025-02-25 00:52:19', '2025-02-25 00:52:19', NULL),
(283, 199, '20252073', 'It was a childhood dream and I was also motivated by my grandfather', 'Values and habits of discipline, determination, will power, visualization and strong grit are highly essential', 'My aim to become a civil servant motivates me', 'My optimism and resolve', 'My problem of procrastination', 'Overthinking and self doubt', 'I am yet to complete the syllabus and it is troubling me', 'As my composite course in SNTCSSC will be completed soon, I will increase my studying hours and will start my thorough revision', 'I have prepared a time table and have started meditation to curb my issue of overthinking', 'Nothing else except my phone', 'Limiting my screen time', 'Keeping my phone away while studying', '2025-02-25 01:17:32', '2025-02-25 01:17:32', NULL),
(284, 88, '20251009', 'I have worked in the field of political consultancy for an year and half during which I identified my interest for a field job, moreover, during the same period I got the opportunity to interact with administrators and civil servants which motivated me to prepare for the civil services.', 'Consistency and Will Power', 'The IAS is a dream job and as this profile can help me bring a change and I will be able to see the change on field during my period of services hence a feeling of satisfaction.', 'Willpower for hardwork, and field experience helps me related various topics of the syllabus well.', 'Lack in self-confidence hence a reason for constant self-doubt thus impacting my efficiency.', 'Lack in self-confidence hence a reason for constant self-doubt thus impacting my efficiency.', 'Revision and analysis of Mock tests.', 'Planning a little better from the second revision onwards, and taking out dedicated time for test analysis.', 'Spending first 2 hours of my study hours for test analysis which could also help me revise and then pick up the subject thought of during subsequent hours of the day.', '1. Health (lack in immunity)\r\n2. Joint family hence occasionally disturbance due to family functions or commitments.', 'I have been trying  to incorporate exercise in my daily routine and secondly try to spend maximum study hours in library.', 'Second Revision onwards (last three months) before D-day should be most productive hence I will overcome the above mentioned distractions before the 27th of February.', '2025-02-25 02:19:28', '2025-02-25 02:19:28', NULL),
(285, 244, 'PCC2025053', 'I want to serve the nation and make a difference. Even though I was not hundred percent sure from day one, but I have always been inclined towards civil services from my childhood days. And ever since I have started my preparation and gone through the details of my country in different domains be it history, or the political system, or how we face economic challenges, my desire to be a civil servant has only increased.', 'I feel discipline, desire, honesty, and being level-headed are the four most essential things. Motivation can be trivial and may not be there all the time because the preparation phase is itself so grueling and long, but if one has all these four qualities, they can really go a long way in this examination.', 'The desire to serve the nation and be amongst those 1% who get the chance to do so motivates me every day and keeps me going.', 'I feel I am mentally tough and have an innate ability to handle pressure, which will really help me in clearing this exam, especially during the times when I get stressed and anxious. Also, my ability to adapt quickly will also help me I feel along with the internal motivation I have. My level-headed nature is also something that is going to be helpful for me.', 'I need to bring in a bit more discipline into my life, apart from getting rid of trivial things or distractions, which I feel I have already worked out. But bringing in discipline is something I am still working on and is still a work in progress.', 'As the syllabus is very long, making a great plan for the entire preparation phase and then revising the topics which is also a part of the plan, is essential. I may struggle with all of that.', 'The same challenge. Since I have started preparing from the end of last year, I have not been able to go through all the subjects. I have given some of the mock tests here even studying a subject for the first time within the week I get before exams.', 'I plan to overcome this by just being more disciplined and being more meticulous when it comes to managing time because that is the only way to overcome this challenge I feel.', 'I have used some tricks like setting an alarm every time I sit to study and some other things which work for me. I have also convinced myself via self-talking that this is the only way for me to overcome this challenge and every aspirant has been through the same and I have to be bull-headed and just do it.', 'Honestly, there used to be quite a few like social media, friends. but I feel I have figured it out pretty well now how to tackle and all of that and still be able to live life without thinking about studies and upsc all the time. The only thing I am struggling with right now is just to be more smart in my time management and be rigid about that.', 'I am already working on it and developed few tricks to overcome them. But the biggest thing for me is to take action and just do it instead of planning a lot because planning takes a lot out of me and when I fail to implement the plan, I feel more disappointed. My current problem is such that only by taking action will I be able to totally overcome them.', 'I am working on this distraction every day and hopefully within a few days(5 days), I will be able to overcome it in totality.', '2025-02-25 03:08:10', '2025-02-25 03:08:10', NULL),
(286, 309, 'NST2025254', 'My aspirations to serve the Nation, the challenges in the Indian Administrative system and the desire to make a meaningful impact on governance and policy.', 'Consistent Study Schedule, Effective Time Management, Regular Revision, Mock Test, Staying Updated with Current Affairs, Answer Writing Practice, and being Honest.', 'when I read newspaper, I get to Know about many crimes and illegal activities done around us.  As I belong from a rural background, so I know how common poor people suffer from these things. I believe I can stop these crimes if I am in service. This Motivates me to give my best every day.', 'My family is my Strength, who continuously support and motivate me when I feel low.', 'I need to improve my Discipline', 'Nothing', 'Lack of revision', 'I have to give more time in revision', 'I am revising everyday along with my studies.', 'Mobile, Family, Consuming excessive Study materials from online sources', 'From next month I will not use mobile phone, stay away from my family and limit the study materials.', 'I am working on it to overcome my distractions.', '2025-02-25 03:11:08', '2025-02-25 03:11:08', NULL),
