(270, 294, 'PCC2025007', 'M.Sc.', 'BOTANY', 'Botany', 2023, 'yes', 'SNTCSSC District study centre- Purulia(2023-24) Coaching partner-Khan study group(KSG), Delhi', 2023, 1, 'no', NULL, 'no', NULL, '30', 1, 'Geography,Environment & Ecology ,Science and technology', 'Economy,History,Art & Culture', 'Polity, Geography, Environment', 'EconomyHistory ,Art&Culture', '1.Vision IAS monthly current affairs magazine  2.Daily news paper analysis provided by Majid Sir', 1, 'yes', 'NO', 1, 'I revise through the SNTCSSC Prelims Crash Course, notes & books, and YouTube videos for clarity and quick revision.', '1. Regular Revision: Lack of revision was a major setback in my first attempt. This time, I have incorporated weekly and monthly revision cycles to ensure I retain what I study effectively. 2. Self-Analysis: I now actively assess my strengths and weaknesses through mock tests and self-reflection. After every test, I analyze my mistakes and work on improving weak areas. 3. PYQs Analysis: Previously, I overlooked the importance of previous years\' questions. Now, I thoroughly analyze PYQs to understand the exam pattern, frequently asked topics, and key concepts, making my preparation more exam-oriented. 4. Strong Foundation in Basics: Initially, my conceptual clarity was weak. I have now strengthened my basics by thoroughly studying NCERTs and standard reference books. 5. Clear Target and Focus: In my first attempt, I lacked a clear direction. Now, I have a well-defined strategy, realistic targets, and a focused study plan to ensure consistent progress. 6. Guidance from a Mentor: One of the biggest gaps in my previous attempt was the lack of mentorship. However, this time, I am fortunate to have found a mentor, Majid Sir, whose guidance has provided me with clarity, direction, and a structured approach to preparation. I feel very grateful and lucky to have his support. Although I have overcome most of these mistakes, I continue to work on them to refine my approach and maximize my chances of success in this attempt.', 'Yes', NULL, 'yes', 'No', '2025-02-24 21:40:06', '2025-02-24 21:40:06', NULL),
